1
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,003
[ Girl Narrating ]
YOUR WHOLE LIFE CAN CHANGE
IN A SECOND,

2
00:04:34,003 --> 00:04:36,505
AND YOU NEVER EVEN KNOW
WHEN IT'S COMING.

3
00:04:38,007 --> 00:04:41,010
BEFORE, YOU THINK YOU KNOW
WHAT KIND OF WORLD THIS IS.

4
00:04:42,011 --> 00:04:45,514
AND AFTER,
EVERYTHING IS DIFFERENT FOR YOU.

5
00:04:48,017 --> 00:04:50,518
NOT BAD, MAYBE,
NOT ALWAYS...

6
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:55,024
BUT DIFFERENT... FOREVER.

7
00:04:55,024 --> 00:04:58,026
???? [ Piano Continues ]

8
00:04:58,026 --> 00:05:01,030
[ Girl ]
I DIDN'T USED TO KNOW THAT...

9
00:05:01,030 --> 00:05:04,033
'TIL THE DAY IT HAPPENED
TO MY FAMILY.

10
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:07,036
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THERE COULD BE
SUCH A THING AS "AFTER."

11
00:05:09,038 --> 00:05:13,541
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT, FOR US,
"BEFORE" WAS ALREADY OVER.

12
00:05:22,551 --> 00:05:25,054
[ Hits Wrong Note ]

13
00:05:36,064 --> 00:05:41,570
???? [ "Chopsticks"
Drowns Out Classical ]

14
00:05:44,072 --> 00:05:47,076
[ Both Laugh ]

15
00:05:49,078 --> 00:05:50,829
[ Giggling ]

16
00:05:52,831 --> 00:05:54,833
T.J., THIS WON'T HURT.
I PROMISE.

17
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,835
THIS IS MY SPECIAL
BOO-BOO LIGHT.

18
00:05:56,835 --> 00:06:00,839
IN FACT, IT'S MAGIC.
DID YOU EVER SEE A MAGIC
BOO-BOO LIGHT BEFORE?

19
00:06:02,841 --> 00:06:05,844
[ Woman ]
HE HAD NO BUSINESS
BEING ON HIS BROTHER'S SLED.

20
00:06:05,844 --> 00:06:08,347
DARN THING'S
BIGGER THAN HE IS.
YOU'RE NEEDED DOWNSTAIRS.

21
00:06:08,347 --> 00:06:10,349
[ People Murmuring ]

22
00:06:10,349 --> 00:06:13,852
T.J.'S A LUCKY BOY,
MRS. FOLEY, BUT I'D
KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.

23
00:06:13,852 --> 00:06:15,854
IF HE COMPLAINS
OF NAUSEA OR DIZZINESS,

24
00:06:16,355 --> 00:06:19,858
OR EVEN IF HE JUST SEEMS
DROWSIER THAN NORMAL,
GIVE ME A CALL, OKAY?

25
00:06:19,858 --> 00:06:22,861
THAT'S NOT MAGIC.
THAT'S JUST A FLASHLIGHT.

26
00:06:23,362 --> 00:06:25,864
OH, YEAH?
HERE. BLOW.

27
00:06:27,366 --> 00:06:29,367
SEE?
[ Giggles ]

28
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:31,370
SEE YOU LATER.

29
00:06:42,381 --> 00:06:44,882
SHE'S GONE, TRYGVE.
NO, DAMN IT.
THERE'S STILL A CHANCE.

30
00:06:44,882 --> 00:06:46,885
[ Trygve ]
GIVE ME THAT.
[ Doctor ]
TRYGVE, SHE'S GONE.

31
00:06:46,885 --> 00:06:49,388
SHE WASN'T GONNA
MAKE IT ANYWAY.

32
00:06:50,389 --> 00:06:52,390
[ Man ]
WE DID OUR BEST.

33
00:06:52,390 --> 00:06:54,393
LET'S BREAK IT DOWN.

34
00:06:54,393 --> 00:06:56,395
WHAT HAPPENED?
[ Doctor ]
SOME BASTARD CLOBBERED HER...

35
00:06:56,395 --> 00:06:58,897
UP NEAR POOR FARM ROAD,
THEN LEFT HER THERE.

36
00:06:58,897 --> 00:07:01,400
SHE WAS LYING IN THE SNOW
BY THAT POND.

37
00:07:03,402 --> 00:07:05,404
DO WE KNOW WHO THIS IS?

38
00:07:05,404 --> 00:07:08,406
[ Trygve ]
MARTHA TAVERNER.

39
00:07:08,907 --> 00:07:10,909
MARTHA TAVERNER.
MM-HMM.

40
00:07:10,909 --> 00:07:13,912
OH. I'VE MET HER.

41
00:07:13,912 --> 00:07:17,416
I EVEN TREATED HER ONCE,
I THINK, WHEN YOU WERE ON
VACATION, TRYGVE. REMEMBER?

42
00:07:17,416 --> 00:07:19,418
YEAH.

43
00:07:25,424 --> 00:07:27,926
[ Trygve ]
HE'S STILL OUT THERE,
WHOEVER DID THIS.

44
00:07:28,427 --> 00:07:30,928
COULD BE ANYWHERE.

45
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:37,902
[ Girl ]
HEY, DAD. "THREE OUNCES
GROUND CUMIN SEED"?

46
00:07:37,902 --> 00:07:40,905
MM-HMM.
YUCK!
WHAT'S CUMIN SEED?

47
00:07:41,406 --> 00:07:42,907
OH-HO-HO-HO.

48
00:07:43,408 --> 00:07:46,410
THAT IS ABSOLUTELY
THE MOST CRUCIAL,

49
00:07:46,410 --> 00:07:50,415
FANTASTIC,
TOP-SECRET INGREDIENT
IN MY ENTIRE CHILI.

50
00:07:50,415 --> 00:07:53,417
[ Door Slamming ]
[ Girl ]
HI, MOM!

51
00:07:53,417 --> 00:07:56,421
HI. JACOB!

52
00:07:59,424 --> 00:08:03,428
JAKE'S PARKING IS GETTING
SLOPPIER THAN EVER.

53
00:08:03,428 --> 00:08:07,932
MAN! HIS CAR
IS ALL OVER THE PLACE.

54
00:08:07,932 --> 00:08:12,437
BEN? I SWEAR I COULD HARDLY
EVEN GET MINE IN THE GARAGE.

55
00:08:12,437 --> 00:08:14,439
PARKING IT RIGHT WOULD FEEL
TOO MUCH LIKE WORK.

56
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:16,940
MM.
[ Chuckles ]

57
00:08:18,943 --> 00:08:20,945
HI.

58
00:08:20,945 --> 00:08:23,448
LET ME HAVE SOME.

59
00:08:23,448 --> 00:08:25,950
HEY, YOU'RE TREMBLING.
MM.

60
00:08:26,451 --> 00:08:28,453
I'M JUST... COLD.
SIT DOWN.

61
00:08:28,453 --> 00:08:31,455
[ Girl ]
DAD, THIS STUFF'S FREAKING OUT!
IN A MINUTE.

62
00:08:31,955 --> 00:08:34,459
CAROLYN, WHAT--
[ Deep Sigh ]

63
00:08:34,459 --> 00:08:36,461
WE HAD AN EVENT
AT THE HOSPITAL TODAY.

64
00:08:36,461 --> 00:08:38,463
[ Doorbell Rings ]
"EVENT"?

65
00:08:38,962 --> 00:08:40,965
DAD, COME QUICK!

66
00:08:40,965 --> 00:08:43,468
[ Doorbell Rings ]
AHHH.

67
00:08:47,471 --> 00:08:49,474
FRAN!
DR. RYAN.

68
00:08:49,474 --> 00:08:53,978
[ Chuckling ]
YOU HAVEN'T CALLED ME "DOCTOR"
SINCE WE FIRST MOVED UP HERE.

69
00:08:57,482 --> 00:08:59,984
HI, MOM.
BEN.
HEY THERE, CHIEF.

70
00:08:59,984 --> 00:09:01,985
OUT OF UNIFORM TODAY.
WHAT'S UP?

71
00:09:01,985 --> 00:09:05,490
UH, SORRY TO BARGE IN
ON YOU LIKE THIS,
RIGHT HERE AT SUPPERTIME.

72
00:09:05,490 --> 00:09:08,493
- GET YOU SOMETHING, FRAN?
A BEER, IF YOU'RE NOT ON DUTY.
- NO, NO, BEN.

73
00:09:08,493 --> 00:09:10,494
THAT'S OKAY.
THANKS. UM--

74
00:09:12,497 --> 00:09:13,998
[ Sighs ]
IS JACOB AROUND?

75
00:09:14,499 --> 00:09:18,502
HE'S UP IN HIS ROOM, I GUESS,
WITH THOSE DAMN HEADPHONES ON.
YOU KNOW JACOB.

76
00:09:18,502 --> 00:09:20,505
YOU DIDN'T
SEE HIM COME IN?
I WAS IN THE STUDIO.

77
00:09:22,507 --> 00:09:25,509
DO YOU NEED HIM FOR SOMETHING?
YOU WANT US TO GET HIM, FRAN?
I'LL GO.

78
00:09:25,509 --> 00:09:27,512
YEAH, GO ON, HONEY.

79
00:09:29,013 --> 00:09:31,015
IS THERE
SOMETHING WRONG?

80
00:09:34,519 --> 00:09:37,522
[ Expelling Air ]
OKAY, UH--

81
00:09:38,022 --> 00:09:41,525
SOMETHING HAPPENED
OUT ON POOR FARM ROAD TODAY.
SOMETHING PRETTY BAD.

82
00:09:41,525 --> 00:09:44,529
A GIRL
GOT HERSELF KILLED.

83
00:09:44,529 --> 00:09:47,031
- I KNOW. I SAW HER.
- WHAT?

84
00:09:47,031 --> 00:09:49,032
WE HAD HER IN E.R.
BEYOND SAVING.

85
00:09:49,032 --> 00:09:51,536
I MEAN, IT WAS--
IT WAS AWFUL.

86
00:09:51,536 --> 00:09:54,038
GEEZ.
THAT'S WHAT I WAS GONNA
TELL YOU WHEN I CAME IN.

87
00:09:54,038 --> 00:09:56,039
GOD, I'M SORRY.
WHAT DOES THAT HAVE TO DO
WITH JACOB?

88
00:09:56,540 --> 00:09:58,042
OH, GOD,
I DON'T--

89
00:09:58,543 --> 00:10:02,046
I DON'T WANNA
HAVE TO TELL YOU THIS.
I REALLY DON'T.

90
00:10:02,547 --> 00:10:04,548
JACOB WAS SEEN
WITH THE GIRL.

91
00:10:04,548 --> 00:10:06,551
HE PICKED HER UP
FROM WORK.

92
00:10:06,551 --> 00:10:10,554
SHE WORKS DOWN
AT JACEY'S AFTER SCHOOL,
MAKING ICE CREAM CONES.

93
00:10:10,554 --> 00:10:14,058
HE CAME BY IN HIS CAR,
AND THEY WENT OFF TOGETHER,
LIKE THEY'D BEEN DOIN'.

94
00:10:14,058 --> 00:10:16,561
AS FAR AS WE KNOW,
RIGHT NOW,

95
00:10:17,061 --> 00:10:19,062
HE WAS THE LAST PERSON
WITH HER.

96
00:10:19,062 --> 00:10:22,066
ARE YOU SAYING JACOB
WAS DATING THAT GIRL,
MARTHA TAVERNER?

97
00:10:22,066 --> 00:10:24,569
NO, NO. WHAT HE'S--
WHAT HE'S SAYING IS HE'S--

98
00:10:24,569 --> 00:10:27,070
[ Chuckles ]
HE'S STANDING HERE
IN OUR KITCHEN...

99
00:10:27,070 --> 00:10:29,073
SAYING THAT HE THINKS
OUR SON WAS--

100
00:10:29,574 --> 00:10:32,076
OH, FOR CRYING
OUT LOUD, FRAN.
BEN, HEY, HEY.

101
00:10:32,577 --> 00:10:35,580
LET'S NOT JUMP THE GUN HERE.
I JUST NEED TO TALK TO HIM.
JACOB!

102
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:38,583
JESUS CHR--

103
00:10:38,583 --> 00:10:40,585
HE'S NOT UP THERE.
I LOOKED ALL OVER.
WELL, THAT'S CRAZY.

104
00:10:40,585 --> 00:10:43,588
I-I-- HIS CAR'S
IN THE GARAGE.
I JUST SAW IT.

105
00:10:43,588 --> 00:10:46,090
YOU HAVE A SPARE
SET OF KEYS
FOR THE CAR?

106
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:48,092
YEAH, I THINK THAT I DO.
DADDY.

107
00:10:48,593 --> 00:10:50,594
SOMETHING'S HAPPENED,
JUDITH, BUT THERE'S BEEN
A MISUNDERSTANDING.

108
00:10:50,594 --> 00:10:52,597
WE'LL EXPLAIN LATER, OKAY?
MM-HMM.

109
00:10:52,597 --> 00:10:55,600
OKAY, WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

110
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,601
DO WHAT?
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

111
00:10:57,601 --> 00:11:01,105
YOU CAN'T GO SNOOPING AROUND
IN SOMEBODY ELSE'S CAR.
LEGALLY, THAT'S MY CAR.

112
00:11:01,105 --> 00:11:03,107
YOU DO NOT HAVE
A SEARCH WARRANT.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

113
00:11:03,608 --> 00:11:07,111
I'M SURE THERE'S SOME
VERY SIMPLE EXPLANATION
FOR ALL OF THIS.

114
00:11:07,111 --> 00:11:11,115
JACOB AND THE TAVERNER GIRL
MUST HAVE SEPARATED SOMEHOW
BEFORE THIS EVEN HAPPENED.

115
00:11:11,115 --> 00:11:13,617
YOU KNOW, MAYBE HE JUST
DROPPED HER OFF SOMEWHERE.

116
00:11:13,617 --> 00:11:17,121
MAYBE SHE GOT OUT
OF THE CAR AND WALKED AWAY.
THERE'S A THOUSAND DIFFERENT--

117
00:11:21,626 --> 00:11:23,127
FRAN, HOW DO WE KNOW
HE'S ALL RIGHT?

118
00:11:25,630 --> 00:11:31,135
MAYBE SOME MADMAN DID SOMETHING
TO BOTH OF THEM, AND MAYBE
JACOB'S HURT, OR HE'S KIDNAPPED.

119
00:11:32,136 --> 00:11:34,138
OH, MY GOD.

120
00:11:34,138 --> 00:11:37,642
CAROLINE, FOR HIS OWN SAKE,
THAT CAR MIGHT GIVE US
SOME ANSWERS.

121
00:11:39,644 --> 00:11:42,646
NO.
[ Gasps ]

122
00:11:42,646 --> 00:11:44,649
[ Sighs ]

123
00:11:44,649 --> 00:11:47,151
YOU'RE HIS PARENTS.
YOU WANNA PROTECT HIM.

124
00:11:47,151 --> 00:11:50,654
I GOT KIDS TOO,
BUT--

125
00:11:50,654 --> 00:11:54,158
BEN, IS THERE SOMETHING
THAT YOU KNOW THAT YOU'RE
NOT TELLIN' ME?

126
00:11:59,162 --> 00:12:01,165
HOW 'BOUT IT, JUDITH?
YOU KNOW ANYTHING--
HEY! HEY!

127
00:12:01,666 --> 00:12:04,168
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
OFF LIMITS! LEAVE HER
OUT OF THIS, OKAY?

128
00:12:04,669 --> 00:12:06,670
OKAY, PLEASE, PLEASE, BEN.
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I KNOW.

129
00:12:06,670 --> 00:12:08,673
IT'S JUST FRAN.
I KNOW
MY SON!

130
00:12:08,673 --> 00:12:11,676
HE'S JUST TRYING TO HELP US
FIND HIM, DARLIN'.
I DON'T WANT IT TO BE LIKE THIS.

131
00:12:11,676 --> 00:12:14,678
BUT IF I HAVE TO,
I WILL GO FIND JUDGE GRADY,
AND I WILL GET A SEARCH WARRANT.

132
00:12:14,678 --> 00:12:16,681
YEAH, YEAH.
YOU DO THAT!
AND I WILL BE
RIGHT BACK HERE.

133
00:12:16,681 --> 00:12:19,684
IT'S OKAY.
OKAY.

134
00:12:19,684 --> 00:12:23,688
SWEETIE, YOU LOOKED UPSTAIRS?
YOU'RE SURE?
YOU LOOKED EVERYPLACE?

135
00:12:31,195 --> 00:12:34,198
[ Car Engine Starts ]

136
00:12:34,198 --> 00:12:36,199
WE SHOULD HAVE LET HIM
LOOK IN THE CAR, BEN.

137
00:12:36,199 --> 00:12:40,204
THE HELL WE SHOULD HAVE.
NOT WITHOUT A LAWYER
TELLING ME I HAVE TO.

138
00:12:40,204 --> 00:12:42,707
LOOK, WE'VE GOT
RIGHTS HERE.

139
00:12:42,707 --> 00:12:46,210
AND WHEREVER HE IS,
WHATEVER THEY THINK HE DID,
JACOB HAS RIGHTS TOO.

140
00:12:46,210 --> 00:12:48,713
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO TAKE THIS
ONE STEP AT A TIME, OKAY?

141
00:12:48,713 --> 00:12:51,715
YOU AND I WILL LOOK
IN THE HOUSE.
TOP TO BOTTOM.

142
00:12:51,715 --> 00:12:53,718
I'LL CHECK OUT
THE GARAGE AND STUDIO.

143
00:12:53,718 --> 00:12:57,221
AND IF HE'S NOT THERE, WE'LL
JUST START CALLING HIS FRIENDS.
CAROLYN.

144
00:12:57,221 --> 00:12:59,723
BETTER CALL
WENDELL TOO. HUH?

145
00:13:23,246 --> 00:13:24,749
[ Squeaking ]

146
00:13:51,775 --> 00:13:55,279
[ Chuckles, Grunts ]

147
00:14:00,283 --> 00:14:02,286
[ Sniffles ]

148
00:14:43,828 --> 00:14:47,330
[ Panting ]

149
00:14:47,330 --> 00:14:49,834
[ Panting ]

150
00:14:53,837 --> 00:14:55,840
OH, NO.

151
00:14:57,842 --> 00:15:00,344
[ Panting ]
OH, JAKE.

152
00:15:01,845 --> 00:15:06,350
[ Panting ]

153
00:15:06,350 --> 00:15:08,768
I KNOW THAT, WENDELL.

154
00:15:09,269 --> 00:15:11,772
[ Judith ]
MOM?
WAIT, WAIT.

155
00:15:11,772 --> 00:15:14,275
WHEN FRAN COMES BACK,
WE'LL BE PERFECTLY--

156
00:15:18,278 --> 00:15:21,282
[ Carolyn ]
I KNOW IT'S A SMALL TOWN,
BUT IT'S OUR TOWN TOO.

157
00:15:23,783 --> 00:15:26,286
HE WILL. I PROMISE.
I PROMISE.

158
00:15:26,286 --> 00:15:28,289
JUST HURRY, OKAY?

159
00:15:28,789 --> 00:15:31,291
LAWYERS.
MOM?

160
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:35,296
YEAH.
JACOB WAS REALLY MAD
THIS MORNING.

161
00:15:35,296 --> 00:15:37,298
SAID HE MIGHT NOT
EVEN GO TO SCHOOL.

162
00:15:42,303 --> 00:15:44,305
WHY?

163
00:15:46,306 --> 00:15:47,807
WHAT HAPPENED?

164
00:15:49,810 --> 00:15:53,314
HE AND DADDY, WELL--

165
00:15:53,314 --> 00:15:56,316
YOU KNOW, THEY,
THEY HAD ANOTHER FIGHT.

166
00:15:58,819 --> 00:16:01,322
WHAT?

167
00:16:01,821 --> 00:16:04,825
YOU KNOW THAT JACOB
WANTS TO RENT A BIG CAR
FOR THE WINTER DANCE...

168
00:16:05,326 --> 00:16:07,328
AND, LIKE, RIDE AROUND
ALL NIGHT?

169
00:16:08,829 --> 00:16:11,331
SO DADDY GOES,
"HOW ARE YOU PLANNING
TO PAY FOR IT?

170
00:16:11,831 --> 00:16:13,834
"WE'VE GOT RULES ABOUT
THIS SORT OF THING, MISTER.

171
00:16:14,335 --> 00:16:17,337
IT'S TIME YOU LEARN TO PAY
YOUR OWN WAY, JACOB."

172
00:16:17,337 --> 00:16:20,841
MOM, HE KNOWS JAKE
COULD NEVER SAVE UP
IN TIME. HE KNOWS THAT.

173
00:16:20,841 --> 00:16:23,344
MM-HMM.
BUT, LIKE, JAKE'S
SUCH A BIG DOPE.

174
00:16:23,344 --> 00:16:26,346
HE ALREADY PROMISED RIDES
TO ALL HIS CREEPY FRIENDS.

175
00:16:26,346 --> 00:16:29,850
HE'S ALREADY BRAGGED
ABOUT IT TO MARTH--
MARTHA?

176
00:16:30,851 --> 00:16:33,853
YOU KNEW ABOUT THIS GIRL?

177
00:16:33,853 --> 00:16:35,856
JUDE, HOW LONG HAVE
THEY BEEN GOING OUT?

178
00:16:35,856 --> 00:16:38,359
SINCE SEPTEMBER.

179
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:41,861
BUT HE MADE ME SWEAR
I WOULDN'T TELL.

180
00:16:44,865 --> 00:16:49,369
JAKE SAID TO DADDY,
"YOU THINK 'CAUSE YOU'RE
THIS BIG ARTIST,

181
00:16:49,369 --> 00:16:52,373
IT'S LIKE RULES DON'T APPLY
TO YOU, BUT THEY SHOULD
ALWAYS APPLY TO ME."

182
00:16:52,373 --> 00:16:54,874
"YOU'RE A HYPOCRITE,"
JAKE SAID.

183
00:16:58,379 --> 00:17:01,382
AND THEN DADDY--
DADDY JUST TOTALLY LOST IT.

184
00:17:02,383 --> 00:17:04,384
BUT IT WAS
NEVER THAT BAD.

185
00:17:08,889 --> 00:17:12,392
OH.
MOM, I'M SO SCARED.

186
00:17:12,392 --> 00:17:15,396
HMM.
YOU DIDN'T SEE
THEIR FACES.

187
00:17:15,396 --> 00:17:18,398
YOU WEREN'T THERE.

188
00:17:18,398 --> 00:17:24,405
WELL, DADDY JUST-- HE WANTS
JACOB TO BE MORE RESPONSIBLE, SO
HE TRIES TO CHALLENGE HIS PRIDE.

189
00:17:24,405 --> 00:17:26,906
MAYBE TOO HARD SOMETIMES,
BUT THAT'S LOVE, JUDE.

190
00:17:27,407 --> 00:17:30,411
[ Sobbing ]
YOU KNOW?
THAT'S LOVE.

191
00:17:50,930 --> 00:17:53,934
[ Sighs ]

192
00:18:08,982 --> 00:18:10,984
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GO!
OKAY.

193
00:18:58,531 --> 00:19:01,535
[ Panting ]

194
00:19:03,036 --> 00:19:08,040
[ Sirens Wailing ]

195
00:20:01,259 --> 00:20:04,263
[ Fran ] I'LL GO ON
UP TO THE HOUSE!
[ Judith ] MOM!

196
00:20:11,771 --> 00:20:13,772
[ Pounding
On The Door ]
OH.

197
00:20:30,288 --> 00:20:32,290
WHAT ARE YA DOIN', BEN?

198
00:20:33,292 --> 00:20:35,294
HAVING A LOOK
AT MY CAR.

199
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:44,302
DON'T I HAVE A RIGHT
TO BE IN MY OWN GARAGE?

200
00:20:44,302 --> 00:20:47,305
HOW LONG YOU
BEEN OUT HERE?

201
00:20:47,305 --> 00:20:49,809
COUPLE OF MINUTES.

202
00:20:49,809 --> 00:20:53,812
ALL I DID WAS LOOK AROUND,
AND I SURE DIDN'T SEE
ANYTHING WRONG EITHER.

203
00:20:55,815 --> 00:20:58,818
- KEYS, BEN.
- WHAT ABOUT THE WARRANT?

204
00:21:00,819 --> 00:21:02,821
OH, BEN--
[ Sighs ]

205
00:21:04,323 --> 00:21:06,325
YOU ARE ASKIN'
FOR TROUBLE ON THIS.

206
00:21:08,827 --> 00:21:11,831
[ Sighs ]
YOU'RE NOT THINKIN' CLEAR.

207
00:21:11,831 --> 00:21:15,834
NOW, HOW CAN I
HELP YOU IF YOU
DON'T EVEN TRUST ME?

208
00:21:15,834 --> 00:21:17,836
IT'S ALL YOURS.

209
00:21:25,844 --> 00:21:27,346
[ Trunk Lid Opening ]

210
00:21:27,847 --> 00:21:31,850
[ Policemen Talking,
Indistinct ]

211
00:21:33,351 --> 00:21:35,354
THIS ALWAYS SUCH A MESS?

212
00:21:36,856 --> 00:21:40,859
[ Ben ]
I'VE GOT SUPPLIES
TO MOVE AROUND. ART STUFF.

213
00:21:44,363 --> 00:21:46,364
I CAN'T USE CAROLYN'S CAR.
SHE HAS A FIT.

214
00:21:46,865 --> 00:21:49,869
AND THE JEEP'S TOO SMALL.
[ Clattering ]

215
00:21:53,371 --> 00:21:55,373
WHAT ABOUT THE FLOOR?

216
00:21:56,374 --> 00:21:58,878
WHERE'D ALL THIS SAWDUST
COME FROM--

217
00:21:58,878 --> 00:22:03,381
ALL THESE LITTLE PIECES
OF NEW WOOD?

218
00:22:03,882 --> 00:22:07,386
[ Sighs ]
YOU THINK I'M STUPID, BEN?
YOU THINK I'M QUAINT?

219
00:22:07,386 --> 00:22:10,388
OKAY. SO I LOOKED IN THERE.

220
00:22:10,388 --> 00:22:13,392
MAYBE SOME SAWDUST
DRIFTED OUT. IS THAT A CRIME?

221
00:22:15,393 --> 00:22:17,395
[ Sighs ]

222
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:23,401
THIS CAR IS
OFFICIALLY IMPOUNDED.

223
00:22:25,403 --> 00:22:27,907
[ Sighs ]
AND I WANNA
TELL YOU SOMETHIN'.

224
00:22:29,408 --> 00:22:32,410
IF IT TURNS OUT
YOUR KID IS IN TROUBLE,

225
00:22:32,911 --> 00:22:35,414
THEN YOU ARE
IN TROUBLE TOO.

226
00:22:35,414 --> 00:22:37,917
NOW LET'S HAVE
A LOOK AT HIS ROOM.

227
00:22:37,917 --> 00:22:40,919
YOU'RE SEARCHING JACOB'S
ROOM? [ Chuckles ]
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT I AM.

228
00:22:43,923 --> 00:22:46,925
[ Fran ]
OHH.
[ Ben ] HEY, IF YOU
FIND HIS BED, LET US KNOW.

229
00:22:46,925 --> 00:22:49,427
WE HAVEN'T SEEN IT
IN YEARS.
I DON'T LIKE
YOUR ATTITUDE.

230
00:22:49,427 --> 00:22:53,932
IT'S NOT EXACTLY WHAT
I WOULD CALL DECENT,
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES.

231
00:22:53,932 --> 00:22:57,435
WELL, WE HAVEN'T HAD
MUCH PRACTICE, FRAN,
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES.

232
00:22:59,438 --> 00:23:02,941
ALL RIGHT, I WANNA LOOK
IN THAT CLOSET, BUT FIRST
I WANNA LOOK IN THIS TRUNK.

233
00:23:06,445 --> 00:23:08,947
[ Fran ]
CHECK THE BOTTOM
OF THIS, INCLUDING HERE.

234
00:23:10,448 --> 00:23:12,450
NOW LET'S GET THE BED.

235
00:23:22,461 --> 00:23:24,963
[ Fran Talking,
Indistinct ]

236
00:23:38,477 --> 00:23:41,479
[ Fran ] FINISH UP
IN HERE, WILL YOU?
[ Police Officer ] YEAH.

237
00:23:46,485 --> 00:23:48,987
OH--

238
00:23:52,491 --> 00:23:54,492
HEY. EXCUSE US.

239
00:23:55,994 --> 00:23:58,496
"THE PREMISES,"
"THE OCCUPANT,"
"A SEARCH--"

240
00:23:58,496 --> 00:24:00,499
NOW MAYBE YOU SEE WHY
I DIDN'T JUST FALL INTO LINE.

241
00:24:00,499 --> 00:24:03,501
IT'S SO STUPID AND USELESS.
WHY AREN'T THEY OUT
LOOKING FOR HIM?

242
00:24:14,012 --> 00:24:17,016
WELL, NOW.

243
00:24:19,017 --> 00:24:21,519
HIDDEN IN
HIS TOP DRAWER.

244
00:24:23,022 --> 00:24:25,023
[ Ben ]
SO?
SO...

245
00:24:25,023 --> 00:24:27,025
THAT'S A LINK,
DON'T YOU THINK?

246
00:24:27,525 --> 00:24:30,529
THIS PROVES THAT
THEY KNEW EACH OTHER.

247
00:24:30,529 --> 00:24:34,032
FRAN, NOBODY'S PRETENDING
THEY DIDN'T.

248
00:24:34,032 --> 00:24:36,034
SORRY I'M LATE.
I'M SO SORRY.

249
00:24:36,534 --> 00:24:40,538
-IFTHAT'S EVEN HER.
- OH, IT'S HER, WENDELL.
IT IS MARTHA TAVERNER.

250
00:24:40,538 --> 00:24:42,540
HERE'S
THE SEARCH WARRANT.

251
00:24:42,540 --> 00:24:45,043
WELL, I WANT A COMPLETE
INVENTORY OF ALL THE ITEMS...

252
00:24:45,043 --> 00:24:48,046
THAT YOU'RE REMOVING
FROM THIS HOUSE,
WITH A SIGNED RECEIPT.

253
00:24:49,547 --> 00:24:51,549
COME ON UP!
OKAY!

254
00:25:03,061 --> 00:25:05,063
OH, CAROLYN.

255
00:25:05,063 --> 00:25:07,065
UH, ONE MORE THING.

256
00:25:08,567 --> 00:25:12,070
WHEN DID YOU LOAN JACOB
YOUR TIRE JACK?

257
00:25:12,070 --> 00:25:14,072
MY--

258
00:25:16,075 --> 00:25:19,077
WELL, I'M JUST WONDERING
WHY A BEAT-UP OLD CHEVY...

259
00:25:19,077 --> 00:25:21,579
HAS THE JACK
FROM A '94 PARK AVENUE.

260
00:25:21,579 --> 00:25:24,083
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
HOLD ON.
DON'T ANSWER THAT.

261
00:25:24,083 --> 00:25:28,586
FRAN, FISHING SEASON STARTS
IN APRIL. LET'S YOU AND I
GO OUTSIDE AND TALK, HUH?

262
00:25:28,586 --> 00:25:31,089
[ Fran ]
LOOK, JACOB, MAY NOT
EVEN HAVE BEEN THERE,

263
00:25:31,089 --> 00:25:34,092
BUT THEY ARE PUTTING
THEMSELVES IN FRONT
OF THE LAW, WENDELL.

264
00:25:34,092 --> 00:25:36,094
THAT DOES NOT HELP ANYBODY.
YOU SEEM TO BE CONDUCTING
A FULL INVESTIGATION.

265
00:25:36,594 --> 00:25:38,596
[ Fran ]
I'M JUST SAYIN' THAT
AS A FRIEND.

266
00:25:38,596 --> 00:25:41,599
[ Door Closes ]
CAROLYN.
PLEASE, COME HERE.

267
00:25:41,599 --> 00:25:44,102
[ Fran, Wendell
CONTINUE CONVERSING,
Indistinct ]

268
00:25:44,102 --> 00:25:47,106
WHAT-- WHAT DOES HE MEAN--
LISTEN, LISTEN,
LISTEN TO ME!

269
00:25:48,607 --> 00:25:50,608
THERE WAS BLOOD
IN THE CAR.
BLOOD?

270
00:25:50,608 --> 00:25:52,610
HER BLOOD ON HIS JACK.
BLOOD EVERYWHERE.

271
00:25:52,610 --> 00:25:55,114
HOW DO YOU KNOW
IT WAS HER BLOOD?
[ Inhaling Deeply ]

272
00:25:55,114 --> 00:25:58,116
[ Carolyn ]
FOR GOD'S SAKE,
IT MIGHT BE HIS.

273
00:25:58,116 --> 00:26:00,618
SHOW ME. I WANNA SEE IT.
NO, NO, NO.
YOU DON'T WANT TO.

274
00:26:01,119 --> 00:26:04,622
BELIEVE ME. ANYWAY,
IT'S BEEN TAKEN CARE OF.

275
00:26:04,622 --> 00:26:07,125
WH-- WHAT?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"TAKEN CARE OF"?

276
00:26:07,125 --> 00:26:09,127
WHATEVER WOULD BURN,
I BURNED.

277
00:26:09,627 --> 00:26:11,130
THE JACK I TOOK APART.
I WASHED IT CLEAN.
OH, NO.

278
00:26:11,630 --> 00:26:14,132
BUT THERE WAS NO TIME TO--
THEY MIGHT FIND SOMETHING
ANYWAY.

279
00:26:14,132 --> 00:26:16,134
FIBERS OR SOME
LITTLE MICROSCOPIC--

280
00:26:16,134 --> 00:26:19,138
GOD ONLY KNOWS WHAT SORT
OF TESTS THEY'VE GOT NOW.
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

281
00:26:19,138 --> 00:26:21,139
IF WE JUST HAD
MORE TIME.
YOU CAN'T JUST--

282
00:26:21,139 --> 00:26:23,641
YOU CAN'T JUST DESTROY EVIDENCE
THAT MIGHT SAVE HIM.

283
00:26:23,641 --> 00:26:27,145
YOU CAN'T JUST-- WHAT IF
YOU'VE DESTROYED EVIDENCE
THAT WOULD PROVE HE'S INNOCENT?

284
00:26:29,647 --> 00:26:31,649
BEN, PLEASE,
JUST STOP ONE MINUTE.

285
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:35,153
PLEASE.
WE HAVE TO THINK.

286
00:26:35,153 --> 00:26:38,656
WE HAVE TO DECIDE.
WHAT? WHAT HAVE WE
GOT TO DECIDE?

287
00:26:40,158 --> 00:26:42,161
NOTHING'S GONNA BRING
THAT GIRL BACK.

288
00:26:42,660 --> 00:26:44,662
I'M SORRY, BUT IT'S
TOO LATE. WE'VE GOT
TO THINK OF JACOB!

289
00:26:44,662 --> 00:26:47,665
BUT JACOB'S INNOCENT.
JACOB'S NOT A KILLER.

290
00:26:47,665 --> 00:26:49,668
IF ANYTHING,
HE'S IN DANGER HIMSELF.

291
00:26:50,168 --> 00:26:52,170
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT THEY
WERE ALONE IN THAT CAR?

292
00:26:52,170 --> 00:26:56,175
SOMEONE ELSE MIGHT HAVE
BEEN THERE AND KILLED
THAT GIRL AND TAKEN JACOB.

293
00:26:56,175 --> 00:26:59,677
AND NOW YOU'RE DOING
EVERYTHING YOU CAN TO KEEP
THE POLICE FROM FINDING HIM.

294
00:26:59,677 --> 00:27:04,183
AND WHAT IF IT WAS
JUST AN ACCIDENT, AND JACOB'S
OFF RUNNING SCARED?

295
00:27:04,183 --> 00:27:06,684
WE DON'T KNOW
THE FACTS, BEN.

296
00:27:07,185 --> 00:27:08,686
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED.

297
00:27:09,187 --> 00:27:11,690
[ Tow Truck Pulling Away ]

298
00:27:13,691 --> 00:27:17,195
OKAY, THEY'RE GONE.
YOU WANNA TELL ME
WHATEVER IT IS YOU KNOW?

299
00:27:21,199 --> 00:27:24,202
[ Wendell ]
HEY, HEY, HEY. LOOK,
LOOK. I'M YOUR FRIEND.

300
00:27:24,202 --> 00:27:26,705
AND I LOVE JACOB.
JESUS.

301
00:27:26,705 --> 00:27:28,706
SAT THROUGH EVERY
DAMN CLASS PLAY OF HIS.

302
00:27:29,207 --> 00:27:32,210
I GAVE HIM 50 BUCKS
LAST YEAR FOR THE BIKE-A-THON.

303
00:27:33,211 --> 00:27:36,214
I'M ON YOUR SIDE.

304
00:27:36,214 --> 00:27:39,717
- WENDELL, THERE IS
SOMETHING YOU SHOULD KNOW.
- HEY!

305
00:27:40,218 --> 00:27:43,721
WHAT IS THAT?
WHAT IS THAT, BEN RYAN?

306
00:27:44,222 --> 00:27:48,226
ARE YOU GONNA PRESUME NOW
TO TELL ME WHEN I CAN SPEAK
AND WHEN I HAVE TO BE QUIET?

307
00:27:48,226 --> 00:27:51,229
- YOU CAN KEEP YOUR OWN TONGUE
IF YOU WANT TO, BUT YOU--
- [ Phone Ringing ]

308
00:27:51,729 --> 00:27:53,731
JACOB!

309
00:27:55,233 --> 00:27:58,736
HELLO? YES.
WHO IS THIS?

310
00:28:01,739 --> 00:28:04,242
[ Sighs ]

311
00:28:04,242 --> 00:28:07,745
UH-- WELL, I HOPE YOU SLEEP
WELL TONIGHT. YOU'RE A PERSON
OF TRUE COMPASSION.

312
00:28:07,745 --> 00:28:11,249
CAROLYN, IT'S BETTER
IF YOU JUST HANG UP.
YES, IT'S
OUR FIRST WELL-WISHER.

313
00:28:11,249 --> 00:28:13,252
YES, YOU ARE.
AREN'T YOU PROUD?

314
00:28:14,252 --> 00:28:17,255
OH. WELL, YOU HAVEN'T
GOT MUCH OF A BRAIN,

315
00:28:17,255 --> 00:28:20,259
BUT YOU'VE GOT
MIGHTY Q-QUICK REFLEXES.

316
00:28:20,259 --> 00:28:24,262
[ Panting, Sobbing ]

317
00:28:24,262 --> 00:28:25,763
IT'S OKAY, HONEY.

318
00:28:25,763 --> 00:28:27,766
IT'S OKAY.

319
00:28:29,267 --> 00:28:33,271
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
[ Sobbing ]

320
00:28:33,771 --> 00:28:35,274
IT'S OKAY.

321
00:28:35,774 --> 00:28:40,278
[ Carolyn Sobbing ]

322
00:29:23,153 --> 00:29:26,657
[ Panting ]

323
00:29:27,157 --> 00:29:29,661
MA'AM?
[ Gasps ]

324
00:29:29,661 --> 00:29:32,663
THE-- WE'VE BEEN
ALL OVER THIS AREA AND...

325
00:29:32,663 --> 00:29:35,165
SOMEBODY JUST
BURIED THEIR DOG THERE.

326
00:29:35,165 --> 00:29:38,168
OH.
WE DUG IT UP
AND PUT IT BACK.

327
00:30:22,212 --> 00:30:24,715
[ Carolyn ]
I'M GOING BACK TO WORK.

328
00:30:26,216 --> 00:30:28,719
WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

329
00:30:30,722 --> 00:30:32,723
THIS IS CRAZY.

330
00:30:35,726 --> 00:30:38,229
WELL, I HAVE TO
LIVE MY LIFE.

331
00:30:38,229 --> 00:30:42,232
AND THIS TOWN HAS ITS NEEDS TOO.
DOESN'T JUST REVOLVE AROUND US
AND OUR PROBLEMS.

332
00:30:44,735 --> 00:30:47,738
I'LL EITHER BE BACK
IN 15 MINUTES
WITH A BLACK EYE...

333
00:30:47,738 --> 00:30:50,240
OR I'LL BE THERE ALL DAY.

334
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:52,242
HEY.
HMM?

335
00:30:52,242 --> 00:30:54,244
I LOVE YOU.

336
00:30:57,748 --> 00:30:59,750
I LOVE YOU.

337
00:31:02,252 --> 00:31:04,254
BYE.
GOOD-BYE.

338
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:12,262
[ Church Bell Tolling ]

339
00:31:12,262 --> 00:31:16,267
[ Bell Tolling ]
[ Children Chattering ]

340
00:31:23,775 --> 00:31:25,275
[ Chattering Stops ]

341
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:32,783
[ Loud Sobbing ]
[ Woman ]
SLOW IT DOWN, OKAY?

342
00:32:09,821 --> 00:32:11,321
[ Groans ]

343
00:32:23,333 --> 00:32:25,336
[ Carolyn ]
JACOB!

344
00:32:36,847 --> 00:32:39,349
WHAT IF WE NEVER
SEE HIM AGAIN?

345
00:32:42,853 --> 00:32:44,354
OH, DARLING.

346
00:32:46,356 --> 00:32:50,861
NO, DON'T LOSE FAITH.
WE JUST HAVE TO BELIEVE
THAT SOMEHOW HE'LL--

347
00:32:51,361 --> 00:32:53,864
HE'LL FIND HIS WAY
BACK TO US. HE WILL.

348
00:32:55,867 --> 00:32:59,369
AND THERE IS SOME OTHER
EXPLANATION FOR ALL THIS.
I KNOW THERE IS.

349
00:33:00,370 --> 00:33:02,372
I KNOW IT.

350
00:33:36,406 --> 00:33:39,910
"DEAR FOLKS, TOOK A LONG TIME
TO GET TO BOSTON...

351
00:33:39,910 --> 00:33:41,912
"IN THE BIG STORM.

352
00:33:41,912 --> 00:33:44,915
"WASN'T SURE WE'D MAKE IT.
I MIGHT MOVE ON.

353
00:33:44,915 --> 00:33:46,917
"I MIGHT HANG OUT HERE
A WHILE.

354
00:33:46,917 --> 00:33:49,920
WILL TRY TO WRITE.
I KNOW YOU DON'T PRAY,
BUT PRAY NOW."

355
00:33:52,422 --> 00:33:55,425
POSTMARKED
THE DAY BEFORE YESTERDAY.

356
00:33:55,425 --> 00:33:59,930
CAROLYN, HE'S ALIVE.
THIS IS CRAZY.
THIS ISN'T JACOB.

357
00:33:59,930 --> 00:34:02,933
THAT'S HIS HANDWRITING.
NO, NO, NO.
SOMEBODY MADE HIM WRITE THIS.

358
00:34:03,433 --> 00:34:05,936
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?
THE POINT IS, AT LEAST
RIGHT NOW, HE'S OKAY.

359
00:34:05,936 --> 00:34:08,438
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
I'M CALLING FRAN.
I-I THINK IT'S IMPORTANT.

360
00:34:08,939 --> 00:34:11,942
FRAN? CAROLYN,
LISTEN TO ME. WILL YOU
JUST LISTEN TO ME?

361
00:34:12,442 --> 00:34:15,445
IF FRAN SEES THIS,
THE FIRST THING HE'LL DO
IS GET A COURT ORDER...

362
00:34:15,445 --> 00:34:17,447
TO INTERCEPT OUR MAIL
AND TAP OUR PHONES.

363
00:34:17,447 --> 00:34:20,450
THEN YOU CAN FORGET
ABOUT EVER HEARING
FROM JAKE AGAIN.

364
00:34:20,450 --> 00:34:23,453
AND THAT'S JUST
FOR STARTERS.

365
00:34:23,453 --> 00:34:25,956
THEY'LL SLAP A MANHUNT
ALL OVER BOSTON.

366
00:34:26,456 --> 00:34:28,959
HE'LL RUN AGAIN.
GOD KNOWS WHERE.

367
00:34:28,959 --> 00:34:32,462
THINK ABOUT IT.
DO WE REALLY
WANT HIM CAUGHT?

368
00:34:35,966 --> 00:34:40,470
I-- I JUST WANT MY BOY BACK.
I JUST WANNA HOLD HIM AGAIN.

369
00:34:40,470 --> 00:34:43,473
I JUST--
I JUST WANT MY BOY.

370
00:34:43,473 --> 00:34:45,976
OH, SHH, SHH, SHH.

371
00:34:45,976 --> 00:34:48,478
[ Weeping ]

372
00:34:51,197 --> 00:34:54,200
[ Register Rings ]
THAT'S OUT OF 30.

373
00:34:57,704 --> 00:34:59,706
TWENTY-SIX, TWENTY-SEVEN,
TWENTY-EIGHT...
IS THAT WHO I THINK IT IS?

374
00:34:59,706 --> 00:35:01,708
TWENTY-NINE, THIRTY.
[ Whispering ]

375
00:35:04,210 --> 00:35:06,212
BEN RYAN.

376
00:35:08,214 --> 00:35:10,216
KEEP YOUR CHIN UP,
YOU HEAR?

377
00:35:14,721 --> 00:35:17,223
SORRY, JOE.
ALL I NEED IS CHANGE.

378
00:35:39,245 --> 00:35:41,247
OH.

379
00:35:49,255 --> 00:35:53,259
GOOD NIGHT, KAREN.
SEE YOU FOR MY 8:00.
UM,
MRS. WEBBER CANCELED, DOCTOR.

380
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:55,261
SHE SAID
YOU'D UNDERSTAND.

381
00:35:57,764 --> 00:36:00,767
OKAY.
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT.

382
00:36:02,769 --> 00:36:05,772
HI, DOCTOR.
T.J. HI.

383
00:36:05,772 --> 00:36:08,775
I GOT A FEVER.
YOU GOT A FEVER?

384
00:36:08,775 --> 00:36:10,777
OH, WHAT YOU--
COME ON, HONEY.

385
00:36:10,777 --> 00:36:12,779
[ Awkward Laugh ]
I'M SORRY.

386
00:36:29,963 --> 00:36:33,750
ST. LOUIS ON MARCH 11.
THAT'S THE THIRD CARD.

387
00:36:33,750 --> 00:36:37,253
THEN HE WAS IN L.A.
JUST TWO DAYS LATER.
HI.

388
00:36:39,756 --> 00:36:41,758
IT'S A NEW ONE.
CALIFORNIA.

389
00:36:47,263 --> 00:36:50,266
WHAT'S THIS DOING OUT?
THIS SPOILS.

390
00:36:53,770 --> 00:36:56,773
THAT'S IT? THAT'S
YOUR WHOLE REACTION?

391
00:36:56,773 --> 00:36:59,275
LOOK, YOU WON'T SHOW THESE
TO FRAN. ALL RIGHT.

392
00:36:59,275 --> 00:37:03,279
BUT YOU WON'T EVEN SHOW THEM
TO WENDELL, BENNY, AND HE'S
OUR LAWYER. HE'S OUR FRIEND.

393
00:37:03,279 --> 00:37:06,783
IF THIS GETS OUT,
WE DON'T KNOW HOW IT
MIGHT BE USED AGAINST HIM.

394
00:37:06,783 --> 00:37:10,286
MMM.
IN FACT, IT MIGHT
COME IN HANDY LATER
THAT WE KEPT QUIET.

395
00:37:10,286 --> 00:37:12,288
HANDY?
[ Phone Ringing ]

396
00:37:12,288 --> 00:37:14,290
WAIT, WAIT.

397
00:37:19,295 --> 00:37:22,799
HELLO. WENDELL.

398
00:37:22,799 --> 00:37:25,802
WHAT'S--

399
00:37:25,802 --> 00:37:29,305
TURN ON THE TV.
CHANNEL 3. YEAH.
YEAH, WE GOT IT.

400
00:37:29,305 --> 00:37:32,809
- ...CROSS AMERICA--
- ???? [ Theme Music ]
- JACOB RYAN,

401
00:37:33,309 --> 00:37:37,313
THE 16-YEAR-OLD HIGHLAND
RESIDENT, WHO IS A SUSPECT IN
THE MURDER OF MARTHA TAVERNER,

402
00:37:37,313 --> 00:37:39,315
WAS A FUGITIVE
FOR FIVE WEEKS.

403
00:37:39,315 --> 00:37:41,818
THE TEENAGER, AS REPORTED
MOMENTS AGO, WAS ARRESTED
THIS AFTERNOON...

404
00:37:41,818 --> 00:37:44,320
- [ Carolyn Gasps ]
-IN THE BUILDING
YOU SEE BEHIND ME.

405
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:46,823
APPARENTLY,
THE YOUNG FUGITIVE WAS HIDING
IN A FRIEND'S APARTMENT.

406
00:37:46,823 --> 00:37:50,326
WE UNDERSTAND THAT HE IS NOW
BEING HELD IN THE JUVENILE
DETENTION CENTER,

407
00:37:50,326 --> 00:37:53,829
AND IT IS EXPECTED
THAT HE WILL BE ARRAIGNED
SOMETIME TOMORROW.

408
00:38:05,842 --> 00:38:07,844
[ Beeping ]

409
00:38:12,849 --> 00:38:14,851
