410
00:38:16,852 --> 00:38:18,855
[ Indistinct Chatter ]

411
00:38:39,374 --> 00:38:41,377
JAKE. JAKE!

412
00:38:41,377 --> 00:38:44,380
HI, SON.
OH, THANK GOD
YOU'RE SAFE.

413
00:38:50,887 --> 00:38:52,889
HOW ARE YOU, SON?

414
00:38:55,391 --> 00:38:58,394
WHERE WERE YOU?

415
00:38:58,394 --> 00:39:00,897
JAKE, FIRST OFF,
YOUR SISTER--

416
00:39:00,897 --> 00:39:04,400
SHE WANTED US TO ASK YOU,
UM, IF THE POSTCARDS--

417
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:09,405
W-WERE YOU REALLY IN
ALL THOSE PLACES, JAKE?

418
00:39:09,405 --> 00:39:12,408
OR WERE YOU HERE THE WHOLE TIME
IN YOUR FRIEND DARREN'S
APARTMENT, HUH?

419
00:39:18,414 --> 00:39:20,416
YOUR DAD ASKED YOU
A QUESTION.

420
00:39:22,418 --> 00:39:24,420
HONEY, ARE YOU
GONNA TALK TO US?

421
00:39:27,423 --> 00:39:30,426
YOU DON'T THINK YOU'RE GONNA
BE ABLE TO HOLD OUT LIKE THIS
FOREVER, DO YOU, JAKE?

422
00:39:30,426 --> 00:39:33,930
POLICEMEN CAN'T HEAR YOU.
AND WE HAVE TOLD THEM NOTHING.

423
00:39:35,932 --> 00:39:37,934
ARE YOU STILL
MAD AT ME?

424
00:39:39,435 --> 00:39:42,939
IS THAT IT?
YOU KNOW YOUR FATHER
HAS STOOD UP FOR YOU.

425
00:39:42,939 --> 00:39:45,441
TELL ME, PLEASE.
DO YOU
REALIZE THAT?

426
00:39:48,443 --> 00:39:50,947
JAKIE!
GODDAMN IT, MISTER.

427
00:39:50,947 --> 00:39:53,950
HAVE YOU ANY IDEA WHAT
YOU'VE PUT US THROUGH?
MAYBE HE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW.

428
00:39:53,950 --> 00:39:56,451
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHY YOU'RE HERE?
HAVE THEY TOLD YOU?

429
00:39:56,451 --> 00:39:58,454
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO MARTHA TAVERNER?

430
00:39:58,454 --> 00:40:00,957
THERE IS A WARRANT FOR YOU
BACK IN HIGHLAND.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

431
00:40:00,957 --> 00:40:05,962
YOU MAY BE ABLE TO COME HOME.
FIRST, THEY JUST HAVE TO HAVE
A HEARING IN FRONT OF A JUDGE.

432
00:40:05,962 --> 00:40:09,966
A-AND WENDELL BYE WILL BE
RIGHT THERE WITH YOU, AND
DADDY AND I WILL BE RIGHT THERE.

433
00:40:09,966 --> 00:40:12,969
AND YOU BETTER SPEAK UP THEN,
JAKE, IN COURT.

434
00:40:13,469 --> 00:40:14,971
JAKE.

435
00:40:16,973 --> 00:40:19,474
CAN YOU LOOK AT US?

436
00:40:20,476 --> 00:40:22,478
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

437
00:40:32,989 --> 00:40:37,493
DO SOME THINKING ABOUT WHAT
YOU'RE GONNA SAY TO WENDELL.
DON'T WASTE HIS TIME TOO.

438
00:40:57,512 --> 00:40:59,515
LET'S GO.

439
00:41:11,027 --> 00:41:13,361
[ Chattering ]

440
00:41:36,384 --> 00:41:38,386
[ Demonstrators ]
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!

441
00:41:38,386 --> 00:41:42,890
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!

442
00:41:42,890 --> 00:41:45,393
NO BAIL!
KILLERS IN JAIL!

443
00:41:45,393 --> 00:41:47,395
NO BAIL!
KILLERS IN JAIL!

444
00:41:47,395 --> 00:41:51,398
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!

445
00:41:51,398 --> 00:41:53,902
LOOK OUT, PLEASE.
GIVE US SOME ROOM.
LOOK OUT.

446
00:41:53,902 --> 00:41:58,405
[ Chanting Continues ]
WHY DID YOU KILL HER?

447
00:42:00,408 --> 00:42:03,411
JACOB RYAN, YOU'VE HEARD
THE CHARGE AGAINST YOU.

448
00:42:03,411 --> 00:42:09,417
IN JUVENILE PROCEEDINGS,
WE ENTER A PLEA OF "TRUE"
OR "NOT TRUE."

449
00:42:09,417 --> 00:42:11,920
HOW SAY YOU
TO THIS CHARGE?

450
00:42:13,921 --> 00:42:17,425
NOT TRUE.
[ Demonstrators Chanting ]

451
00:42:21,428 --> 00:42:24,933
JACOB RYAN
IS A LONGTIME RESIDENT.

452
00:42:24,933 --> 00:42:28,435
HE'S A FINE STUDENT.
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN
OF FLAWLESS CHARACTER.

453
00:42:28,435 --> 00:42:31,439
AND HE IS STILL,
AT THE MOMENT, A MINOR,

454
00:42:31,439 --> 00:42:35,943
AND, THEREFORE,
WE RESPECTFULLY REQUEST
THAT HE BE RELEASED ON BOND.

455
00:42:36,443 --> 00:42:38,446
JACOB RYAN
IS CHARGED...

456
00:42:38,947 --> 00:42:42,951
WITH A TERRIBLE AND
ALMOST UNTHINKABLE CRIME.

457
00:42:42,951 --> 00:42:47,956
MOREOVER, THE PEOPLE
WILL PROVE THAT HE
EXACERBATED THAT CRIME...

458
00:42:47,956 --> 00:42:49,958
AFTER THE FACT...

459
00:42:49,958 --> 00:42:55,463
BY HIS CUNNING, DELIBERATE
AND COLD-BLOODED DESTRUCTION
OF EVIDENCE.

460
00:42:57,966 --> 00:43:00,468
NO PARENT
IN THIS TOWN...

461
00:43:00,468 --> 00:43:03,471
AND SURELY NO DAUGHTER
COULD FEEL SAFE...

462
00:43:03,972 --> 00:43:06,974
WITH JACOB RYAN
ON THE LOOSE AGAIN.

463
00:43:06,974 --> 00:43:09,978
THE PEOPLE URGE
THAT BAIL BE DENIED.

464
00:43:11,479 --> 00:43:13,981
MARION, I'M JUST
NOT PERSUADED...

465
00:43:13,981 --> 00:43:17,986
THIS BOY IS A THREAT
TO THE GENERAL COMMUNITY.

466
00:43:18,486 --> 00:43:23,491
YOUR HONOR,
I WAS ALSO THINKING
OF THEIR THREAT TO HIM.

467
00:43:25,493 --> 00:43:27,996
DEFENDANT, PLEASE RISE.

468
00:43:30,497 --> 00:43:33,001
PRETRIAL RELEASE GRANTED.

469
00:43:34,502 --> 00:43:37,504
BOND SET AT $250,000.

470
00:43:38,505 --> 00:43:42,510
?? YOU SAY YOU FEEL
SO DISTORTED ??

471
00:43:42,510 --> 00:43:45,512
]
???? [ Continues, Indistinct

472
00:43:50,018 --> 00:43:54,022
NOW LISTEN, MISTER. YOU CAN DO
WHATEVER THE HELL YOU WANT
WITH YOUR CATATONIC SELF,

473
00:43:54,022 --> 00:43:56,024
BUT DON'T EVEN THINK
ABOUT OPENING THIS DOOR.

474
00:43:56,524 --> 00:43:58,526
YOU HEAR ME?
[ Whispering ]
OH, BEN.

475
00:43:58,526 --> 00:44:01,528
JUDE!

476
00:44:01,528 --> 00:44:04,032
JACOB!
I MADE YOU SOME COOKIES!

477
00:44:10,038 --> 00:44:13,541
- JACOB?
-[ Carolyn ]
MAYBE YOU--

478
00:44:13,541 --> 00:44:17,045
MAYBE YOU WANNA HAVE
SOME SOUP FIRST OR S--

479
00:44:17,045 --> 00:44:19,047
A SANDWICH OR SOMETHING.

480
00:44:21,049 --> 00:44:23,550
MOM, WHAT'S WRONG
WITH HIM?

481
00:44:26,554 --> 00:44:29,557
I THINK WE JUST HAVE TO
GIVE HIM A FEW DAYS, SWEETIE.

482
00:44:37,065 --> 00:44:39,066
WHEN WE FOUGHT
THAT MORNING,

483
00:44:42,070 --> 00:44:44,572
I RAISED MY FIST
TO HIM.

484
00:44:44,572 --> 00:44:46,573
I WOULD'VE HIT HIM.

485
00:44:46,573 --> 00:44:49,077
AND WE BOTH
KNEW IT, CAROLYN.

486
00:44:52,580 --> 00:44:55,583
I SENT HIM OUT
INTO THE WORLD
IN THAT KIND OF RAGE.

487
00:44:57,085 --> 00:45:01,588
BUT YOU DIDN'T, BENNY.
YOU DIDN'T HIT HIM.

488
00:45:01,588 --> 00:45:05,593
AND PEOPLE DO FIGHT.
THEY ARGUE ALL THE TIME.

489
00:45:05,593 --> 00:45:09,096
IF I'M TO BLAME
FOR THIS, HOW CAN I
EVER MAKE IT UP TO HIM?

490
00:45:09,096 --> 00:45:11,099
NO.

491
00:45:11,599 --> 00:45:14,102
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED YET.

492
00:45:15,603 --> 00:45:18,105
IF WE START BLAMING
OURSELVES, OR, OR EACH OTHER,

493
00:45:18,105 --> 00:45:20,608
HOW ARE WE
GONNA GET THROUGH THIS?

494
00:45:24,111 --> 00:45:28,116
WHEN HE'S READY
AND WHEN HE'S ABLE, HE'LL
TELL US WHAT HAPPENED. HE WILL.

495
00:45:29,117 --> 00:45:31,618
RIGHT NOW...

496
00:45:31,618 --> 00:45:35,123
THE ONLY IMPORTANT THING
IS THAT WE'RE ALL TOGETHER
AGAIN AND HE'S HOME.

497
00:45:39,126 --> 00:45:41,629
HE'S HOME.
HE'S HOME.

498
00:46:33,180 --> 00:46:35,183
[ Whimpering ]

499
00:46:37,185 --> 00:46:39,687
[ Weeping ]

500
00:46:39,687 --> 00:46:41,688
[ Wendell ]
THEY GOT EYEWITNESSES.

501
00:46:41,688 --> 00:46:46,194
THEY'RE NOT CLAIMING
TO HAVE SOMEONE WHO
ACTUALLY SAW THE MURDER.

502
00:46:46,194 --> 00:46:49,696
AT LEAST NOT YET.
THEN WHAT, EXACTLY, DO THESE
PEOPLE CLAIM TO HAVE SEEN?

503
00:46:49,696 --> 00:46:53,701
THE TWO OF THEM
IN HIS CAR, I WOULD GUESS.

504
00:46:54,202 --> 00:46:57,704
HIS CAR STOPPED MAYBE
UP ON, UH, POOR FARM ROAD?

505
00:47:01,209 --> 00:47:05,713
PROSECUTOR SAYS THEY HAVE PROOF
THAT JACOB DESTROYED EVIDENCE.

506
00:47:05,713 --> 00:47:08,716
WELL, SHE
HAS TO SAY THAT,
DOESN'T SHE?

507
00:47:08,716 --> 00:47:12,219
- THEY STILL HAVEN'T FOUND
THE MURDER WEAPON.
- BUT, BUT SURELY...

508
00:47:12,219 --> 00:47:14,222
THAT HELPS OUR, OUR CASE.

509
00:47:14,222 --> 00:47:17,225
- I MEAN, YOU'RE SAYING THAT
THEY'VE GOT A LOUSY CASE.
- CIRCUMSTANTIAL, YES.

510
00:47:17,225 --> 00:47:19,226
I'M SAYIN' THAT'S POSSIBLE.

511
00:47:19,226 --> 00:47:22,730
THEN I DON'T UNDERSTAND,
WENDELL. WHY ARE YOU
DROPPING OUT ON US?

512
00:47:23,731 --> 00:47:26,733
[ Ironic Laugh ]
I WOULDN'T, UH--

513
00:47:28,736 --> 00:47:30,738
IT'S NOT THAT.

514
00:47:32,240 --> 00:47:34,741
LOOK, I-I--

515
00:47:34,741 --> 00:47:37,245
I DO MORTGAGE CLOSINGS.

516
00:47:37,745 --> 00:47:39,247
YOU NEED
AN EXPERT NOW.

517
00:47:39,747 --> 00:47:41,748
CRIMINAL GUY.

518
00:47:41,748 --> 00:47:45,253
AND BELIEVE ME, THIS GUY
I'M TELLIN' YOU ABOUT--

519
00:47:45,253 --> 00:47:47,255
HE IS THE BEST.

520
00:47:47,255 --> 00:47:49,256
UH, PANOS DEMERIS.

521
00:47:49,256 --> 00:47:51,759
GREEK-AMERICAN.
LIVES OVER IN SPRINGFIELD.

522
00:47:57,764 --> 00:48:00,268
HE'S LOST MAYBE ONE CASE
IN HIS WHOLE LIFE.

523
00:48:02,270 --> 00:48:05,772
HE'LL HAVE JACOB'S JURY
VOTING FOR SAINTHOOD.

524
00:48:05,772 --> 00:48:10,778
AND WHAT ABOUT THE TRUTH
OF WHAT HAPPENED?
DOESN'T THAT MATTER?

525
00:48:13,780 --> 00:48:17,285
THE TRUTH, MRS. RYAN?
THE TRUTH ISN'T ALWAYS
SO SIMPLE.

526
00:48:31,799 --> 00:48:36,303
I JUST MEANT DO YOU HAVE TO
BELIEVE SOMEONE IS INNOCENT
IN ORDER TO TAKE HIS CASE?

527
00:48:36,303 --> 00:48:39,807
A LOT OF MY CLIENTS HAVEN'T BEEN
INNOCENT OF ANYTHING YOU'D CARE
TO LAY ON THEM...

528
00:48:40,308 --> 00:48:42,809
SINCE THEY WERE FIVE YEARS OLD,
BUT THEY STILL DESERVE
A GOOD DEFENSE, RIGHT?

529
00:48:43,310 --> 00:48:46,314
DO YOU MIND IF I EAT
WHILE WE TALK?

530
00:48:48,816 --> 00:48:52,820
IS THIS LATE LUNCH,
MR. DEMERIS, OR
EARLY DINNER?

531
00:48:53,821 --> 00:48:56,824
THIS IS BREAKFAST, I THINK.

532
00:48:56,824 --> 00:49:00,328
I HAD A PRETRIAL MEETING
AND NEVER DID STOP.

533
00:49:00,828 --> 00:49:03,331
OKAY, SO...
YOUR SON, JACOB.

534
00:49:05,332 --> 00:49:09,337
NOW FROM WHAT
YOU'VE TOLD ME, HE SEEMS
LIKE A PRETTY REGULAR KID.

535
00:49:09,337 --> 00:49:12,839
I MEAN EVEN THESE SILENCES,
YOU KNOW? HOPING IF HE
HANGS TOUGH LONG ENOUGH,

536
00:49:13,340 --> 00:49:15,843
MAYBE THIS WHOLE THING
WILL JUST DISAPPEAR?

537
00:49:15,843 --> 00:49:18,346
[ Chuckling ]
TEENAGERS, HUH?
GOD HELP US.

538
00:49:19,347 --> 00:49:21,348
BUT, UH, LET ME--

539
00:49:21,348 --> 00:49:25,353
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.
NOW, PLEASE, TAKE THIS AS
A NEUTRAL QUESTION, OKAY?

540
00:49:25,853 --> 00:49:29,356
IT'S NOT AN ACCUSATION
OF ANY KIND, BUT-- ANGER.

541
00:49:29,356 --> 00:49:33,361
DOES JACOB HAVE ANY PARTICULAR
PROBLEM EXPRESSING HIS ANGER?

542
00:49:33,361 --> 00:49:35,862
DOES HE TEND TO KEEP THINGS
BOTTLED UP?

543
00:49:36,363 --> 00:49:40,368
DOES HE EVER JUST EXPLODE?
YOU SEE, I'M ASKING YOU BECAUSE
IF THERE'S ANY HISTORY HERE,

544
00:49:40,368 --> 00:49:43,370
I MEAN EVEN JUST A WHIFF,
I HAVE TO HEAR IT FROM YOU.

545
00:49:43,370 --> 00:49:46,374
NOT SOME PROSECUTOR.
NO, HE--
THERE'S NO HISTORY.

546
00:49:46,374 --> 00:49:50,378
JACOB'S A VERY--
HE'S A VERY KIND PERSON.

547
00:49:50,378 --> 00:49:52,879
DECENT. CARING.
YOU'D LIKE HIM.
SURE, SURE.

548
00:49:53,380 --> 00:49:56,884
BUT YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND,
MR. AND MRS. RYAN-- I'M SORRY.
IS IT "MR." AND "DR."?

549
00:49:56,884 --> 00:50:00,387
BEN AND CAROLYN.
OKAY. NOW YOU
HAVE TO UNDERSTAND:

550
00:50:00,387 --> 00:50:04,892
JURIES, IN CASES
OF THIS NATURE, THEY TEND
TO BE VERY EMOTIONAL.

551
00:50:05,393 --> 00:50:09,397
THEY TEND TO FEEL THAT
WHERE THERE'S SMOKE,
THERE'S FIRE.

552
00:50:09,397 --> 00:50:14,401
HEY. I COULD BE UP THERE,
ARGUING THAT JACOB IS THE MOST
PERFECT KID IN THE WORLD.

553
00:50:14,401 --> 00:50:16,403
THAT'S ONE STRATEGY.
BUT WHAT THEY'LL BE THINKING,

554
00:50:16,403 --> 00:50:18,906
WHAT THEY'LL SEE
IN THEIR MIND'S EYE...

555
00:50:21,408 --> 00:50:23,910
AND NEVER FORGET IS THIS.

556
00:50:25,413 --> 00:50:27,415
YOU CAN'T--
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

557
00:50:27,415 --> 00:50:30,917
NO, DR. RYAN, I'M--
YOU CANNOT JUST SIT HERE AND EAT
A SANDWICH AND DISPLAY SUCH--

558
00:50:31,418 --> 00:50:33,421
- HOW DO YOU EXPECT US
TO SURVIVE THIS?
- DR. RYAN.

559
00:50:33,421 --> 00:50:35,923
I'M NOT BEING UNSYMPATHETIC.
DON'T INFER THAT.

560
00:50:35,923 --> 00:50:39,927
BUT THIS HAS GOT NOTHING TO DO
WITH SYMPATHY. I THOUGHT YOU
TOLD ME YOU'D SEEN THIS CORPSE.

561
00:50:39,927 --> 00:50:43,431
THIS IS NOT JUST ANY CORPSE.
THIS IS A GIRL THAT I KNEW,
THAT I ONCE TREATED.

562
00:50:43,431 --> 00:50:45,432
JUST BECAUSE YOU SEE THIS KIND
OF THING EVERY DAY--

563
00:50:45,932 --> 00:50:49,937
YOU SPEND ALL YOUR TIME
WITH VIOLENT, HORRIBLE PEOPLE,
BUT WE DON'T, MR. DEMERIS.

564
00:50:49,937 --> 00:50:51,938
NO? WELL, THEN,
YOU'RE VERY LUCKY.

565
00:50:51,938 --> 00:50:54,941
I'M A PHYSICIAN, AND THERE ISN'T
MUCH I HAVEN'T SEEN, BUT THIS IS
MY SON YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

566
00:50:55,443 --> 00:50:58,446
YOU MAY LIKE TO REMEMBER,
DR. RYAN, IT'S ALWAYS
SOMEBODY'S SON.

567
00:50:58,446 --> 00:51:02,449
DON'T YOU PATRONIZE ME, SIR,
BECAUSE I CAN--
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.

568
00:51:02,950 --> 00:51:05,453
LET'S CALM DOWN.
ALL OF US. CAROLYN.

569
00:51:05,453 --> 00:51:09,456
THIS ISN'T
GETTING US ANYWHERE.
COME ON, HONEY.

570
00:51:09,456 --> 00:51:11,959
LOOK, I'M SORRY, FOLKS.

571
00:51:11,959 --> 00:51:14,961
BUT IF YOU DON'T
LIKE ME NOW,

572
00:51:15,462 --> 00:51:18,466
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA SAY
WHEN I HAVE TO GET UP
IN FRONT OF THAT JURY...

573
00:51:18,466 --> 00:51:23,970
AND ARGUE THAT YOUR SON
IS NOT GUILTY BY REASON OF
DIMINISHED MENTAL CAPACITY?

574
00:51:25,472 --> 00:51:27,475
THAT HE WAS DRUNK.
STONED.

575
00:51:27,475 --> 00:51:29,976
HEY, HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.
YES, BOMBED OUT OF
HIS SKULL ON CRACK.

576
00:51:30,477 --> 00:51:33,981
MY SON DOES NOT DO DRUGS.
HE MAY BE YOUR SON, MR. RYAN,
BUT HE WOULD BE MY CLIENT,

577
00:51:33,981 --> 00:51:37,484
AND I WOULD NOT ASK
YOUR PERMISSION FOR HOW
I CHOOSE TO DEFEND HIM.

578
00:51:37,484 --> 00:51:40,987
I'M GONNA HAVE TO DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES.

579
00:51:40,987 --> 00:51:45,992
AND IF YOU DON'T LIKE
MY STYLE, WAIT 'TIL
YOU HEAR THE PROSECUTION.

580
00:51:47,494 --> 00:51:49,997
LISTEN, DR. RYAN,
YOU WANNA JUMP IN
THE TRENCHES WITH ME?

581
00:51:49,997 --> 00:51:52,500
WELL, YOU BETTER MUSCLE UP.

582
00:51:52,999 --> 00:51:58,506
LOSE YOUR BEDSIDE MANNER
AND TRUST ME TO BE AS GOOD
AT MY JOB AS YOU ARE AT YOURS.

583
00:52:06,013 --> 00:52:10,517
WILL YOU DO IT, MR. DEMERIS?
WILL YOU TAKE OUR CASE?

584
00:52:12,520 --> 00:52:14,522
FOR YOUR SON, YEAH.

585
00:52:16,523 --> 00:52:19,025
YEAH, I'LL DEFEND JACOB.

586
00:52:30,037 --> 00:52:31,538
JAKE?

587
00:52:32,038 --> 00:52:35,042
I KNOW YOU DON'T
WANNA TALK, BUT I
JUST NEED TO SEE YOU.

588
00:52:38,545 --> 00:52:40,547
CAN I COME UP?
PLEASE?

589
00:53:09,075 --> 00:53:11,077
CAN I JUST ASK YOU
ONE QUESTION?

590
00:53:15,082 --> 00:53:17,083
DID YOU EVER REALLY
GO ANYWHERE, JAKE?

591
00:53:21,589 --> 00:53:25,091
OKAY. THAT'S COOL.
I UNDERSTAND.

592
00:53:27,594 --> 00:53:30,097
BUT JUST SO YOU KNOW,

593
00:53:30,097 --> 00:53:33,600
WHEN YOU WERE
IN THAT JAIL,
I TRIED TO COME.

594
00:53:34,601 --> 00:53:36,604
THEY WOULDN'T LET ME.

595
00:53:36,604 --> 00:53:39,606
JAKE, I REALLY
WANTED TO SEE YOU.

596
00:53:39,606 --> 00:53:43,109
THEY ACT LIKE THEY HAVE TO
PROTECT ME FROM ALL OF THIS.

597
00:53:43,109 --> 00:53:46,113
SURE. THEY CAN'T EVEN
PROTECT THEMSELVES.

598
00:53:48,114 --> 00:53:51,619
AND I HEAR PLENTY.
I KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON.

599
00:53:53,120 --> 00:53:55,622
LIKE...

600
00:53:55,622 --> 00:53:58,124
MOM'S HAD TO CLOSE
HER OFFICE.

601
00:53:58,124 --> 00:54:00,628
SHE SAYS IT'S
JUST TEMPORARY.

602
00:54:00,628 --> 00:54:02,629
SURE.
GIMME A BREAK.

603
00:54:05,131 --> 00:54:08,135
WELL, ANYWAY,
THAT'S ALL.

604
00:54:08,135 --> 00:54:11,638
I JUST WANTED TO ASK
ABOUT THE POSTCARDS.
NO BIG DEAL.

605
00:54:13,640 --> 00:54:16,143
JUDE, WAIT. DON'T GO.

606
00:54:16,644 --> 00:54:21,147
ONCE OR TWICE A WEEK,
I'D TAKE THE TRAIN
OUT TO LOGAN AIRPORT.

607
00:54:21,147 --> 00:54:25,152
THEN I'D FIND A FLIGHT THAT WAS
GOIN' TO WHERE I WANTED TO GO.

608
00:54:25,152 --> 00:54:29,155
AND THEN I'D FIND SOMEBODY
THAT WOULDN'T MIND MAILING A
CARD FOR ME WHEN THEY GOT THERE.

609
00:54:31,659 --> 00:54:35,161
AND I SAID THAT
I'M HOME FROM VACATION,
AND I FORGOT TO SEND THIS...

610
00:54:35,662 --> 00:54:39,166
AND I DON'T WANT MY PARENTS
TO THINK I DON'T MISS 'EM.

611
00:54:39,667 --> 00:54:41,668
AND THEN, LIKE, I'D SIT
IN ONE OF THOSE CHAIRS,
YOU KNOW?

612
00:54:41,668 --> 00:54:44,170
IN THE WAITING AREA
AT THE AIRPORT.

613
00:54:48,175 --> 00:54:50,176
I'D SHUT MY EYES LIKE THIS...

614
00:54:52,178 --> 00:54:54,181
AND SIT.

615
00:54:57,183 --> 00:54:59,185
I WENT THERE WITH 'EM.

616
00:55:00,688 --> 00:55:03,690
I WENT TO
ALL THOSE PLACES, JUDE.

617
00:55:06,693 --> 00:55:09,196
YOU WON'T SAY ANYTHING,
WILL YOU?

618
00:55:09,196 --> 00:55:11,197
NOBODY ELSE
WOULD UNDERSTAND.

619
00:55:30,049 --> 00:55:32,052
[ Phone Rings ]

620
00:55:32,052 --> 00:55:34,053
WAIT.

621
00:55:35,555 --> 00:55:37,056
[ Rings ]

622
00:55:38,559 --> 00:55:40,561
HELLO.

623
00:55:40,561 --> 00:55:42,562
[ Laughs ]

624
00:55:44,063 --> 00:55:47,568
YES, SIR, I SEE.
OH, THAT'S VERY BIBLICAL.

625
00:55:47,568 --> 00:55:51,571
AND I TAKE IT
YOU WOULD LIKE TO CAST
THE FIRST ONE, HUH?

626
00:55:53,573 --> 00:55:56,577
NOW, I WANT YOU TO
LISTEN VERY CAREFULLY--
NO, NO, YOU LISTEN.

627
00:55:57,076 --> 00:55:59,579
I WANT YOU TO KNOW,
YOU GOOD CITIZEN,
THAT MY SON IS INNOCENT.

628
00:56:00,079 --> 00:56:03,584
HE'S A FREE YOUNG MAN,
LEGALLY HERE ON BOND,
AGAINST WHOM NOTHING HAS BEEN--

629
00:56:04,084 --> 00:56:05,585
NO, NO. YOU'RE WRONG.

630
00:56:06,085 --> 00:56:10,090
UNLESS HE'S CONVICTED
IN A COURT OF LAW, HE IS
NO MORE GUILTY THAN YOU ARE.

631
00:56:10,591 --> 00:56:13,593
SO SLEEP TIGHT, PAL,
AND HEY, HAVE A WONDERFUL
TIME IN CHURCH.

632
00:56:13,593 --> 00:56:16,095
[ Hangs Up Receiver ]

633
00:56:16,095 --> 00:56:18,098
YEAH, DAD.
YOU'RE SO COOL.

634
00:56:18,098 --> 00:56:20,099
YOU REALLY
BELIEVE THAT?

635
00:56:26,607 --> 00:56:29,609
WELL, OF--
OF COURSE I DO.

636
00:56:29,609 --> 00:56:31,611
OUR WHOLE SYSTEM
OF JUSTICE--

637
00:56:31,611 --> 00:56:34,114
I DON'T MEAN OUR SYSTEM.
I MEAN ABOUT ME.

638
00:56:34,114 --> 00:56:36,616
DO YOU BELIEVE
THAT I'M NOT GUILTY?

639
00:56:38,618 --> 00:56:40,621
JAKE,

640
00:56:40,621 --> 00:56:42,623
I DON'T KNOW.

641
00:56:42,623 --> 00:56:44,624
BUT--

642
00:56:44,624 --> 00:56:47,628
WELL, NOW THAT
YOU'RE HERE, WE CAN--

643
00:56:47,628 --> 00:56:49,630
WE CAN TALK ABOUT THAT.

644
00:56:49,630 --> 00:56:53,132
BUT WHATEVER THE TRUTH IS,
WE'RE STANDING BY YOU.

645
00:56:53,633 --> 00:56:56,637
ABSOLUTELY.
OH, THAT'S JUST A BUNCH
OF SENTIMENTAL BULLSHIT.

646
00:56:56,637 --> 00:57:00,139
I MEAN ME.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?
HEY. HEY, NOT SO FAST.

647
00:57:00,139 --> 00:57:02,141
[ Carolyn ]
"SENTIMENTAL BULLSHIT"?

648
00:57:02,141 --> 00:57:05,645
EVERYBODY'S PARENTS
SAY STUFF LIKE THAT.
DO THEY? DO THEY REALLY?

649
00:57:05,645 --> 00:57:09,148
AND DO THEY HIDE THE WEAPON
AND DESTROY EVIDENCE...
CAROLYN.

650
00:57:09,148 --> 00:57:11,151
AND LIE
TO THE POLICE?

651
00:57:11,151 --> 00:57:14,153
DO THEY, INDEED?
YOU KNOW THIS
FOR A FACT?

652
00:57:19,660 --> 00:57:23,663
HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO JUST
SIT HERE AND TALK ABOUT
KILLING SOMEBODY?

653
00:57:24,163 --> 00:57:27,668
JAKE, STOP RUNNING.
PLEASE.

654
00:57:28,668 --> 00:57:31,170
YOU'RE HOME NOW.
STOP RUNNING.

655
00:57:32,171 --> 00:57:35,676
IF I TELL YOU
WHAT HAPPENED--
IT WASN'T ME.

656
00:57:37,176 --> 00:57:40,680
[ Sighs ]
IT WASN'T ME, ALL RIGHT?

657
00:57:51,191 --> 00:57:54,193
WE HUNG OUT A LOT
THIS YEAR.

658
00:57:54,193 --> 00:57:57,197
I KEPT MEANING
TO TELL YOU GUYS.

659
00:57:57,197 --> 00:57:59,699
I WANTED YOU TO KNOW,
BUT--

660
00:57:59,699 --> 00:58:02,702
I TOLD MARTHA YOU GUYS
WERE COOL,

661
00:58:02,702 --> 00:58:06,206
BUT THE IDEA OF HAVING TO
MEET YOU, CONVERSE WITH YOU,
IT JUST SPOOKED HER SOMEHOW.

662
00:58:08,708 --> 00:58:12,212
THAT DAY WE HAD
A TERRIBLE ARGUMENT.

663
00:58:14,714 --> 00:58:19,720
[ Sighs ] FROM THE MOMENT
I PICKED HER UP AT THE
ICE CREAM SHOP AT JACEY'S,

664
00:58:19,720 --> 00:58:23,723
SHE WAS ON MY CASE ABOUT
NOT HAVING A RENTAL CAR
FOR THE WINTER DANCE.

665
00:58:23,723 --> 00:58:29,229
SHE WAS SAYING IT'S YOUR WAY,
OURS,OF FINALLY SAYING
SHE'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH FOR ME.

666
00:58:30,229 --> 00:58:32,231
[ Jacob Sighs ]

667
00:58:33,733 --> 00:58:37,236
[ Sighs ]
I-I TRIED TO EXPLAIN TO HER,
BUT SHE JUST--

668
00:58:37,737 --> 00:58:40,740
SHE KEPT YELLING AT ME
AS I WAS TRYING TO DRIVE.

669
00:58:40,740 --> 00:58:44,244
THEN SHE SAID,
"PULL OVER RIGHT HERE."

670
00:58:47,747 --> 00:58:49,248
[ Jacob ]
AND IT TURNS OUT,

671
00:58:49,749 --> 00:58:52,752
I'M NOT THE ONE
SHE'S MAD AT, REALLY.

672
00:58:52,752 --> 00:58:56,255
SHE'S MAD AT EVERYONE
AND EVERYTHING.

673
00:58:56,255 --> 00:59:00,259
GOD, ESPECIALLY,
FOR LETTING THIS HAPPEN TO HER,
'CAUSE IT TURNS OUT--

674
00:59:00,760 --> 00:59:02,762
I'M PREGNANT.

675
00:59:09,268 --> 00:59:12,271
[ Jacob ]
IT GETS EVEN MORE
COMPLICATED.

676
00:59:13,273 --> 00:59:16,275
'CAUSE SHE DIDN'T THINK
IT WAS OURS.

677
00:59:16,275 --> 00:59:20,279
SHE WOULDN'T SAY
WHOSE IT MIGHT BE, BUT...

678
00:59:20,279 --> 00:59:23,282
OBVIOUSLY SHE'S BEEN,
YOU KNOW--

679
00:59:25,284 --> 00:59:27,787
GETTING AROUND.

680
00:59:27,787 --> 00:59:30,290
I NEVER EVEN
HAD A CLUE.

681
00:59:30,290 --> 00:59:34,293
SHE FIGURED IT WASN'T
OURS BECAUSE WE WERE
ALWAYS SO CAREFUL.

682
00:59:35,795 --> 00:59:37,798
SO SHE'S GETTING
ALL WOUND UP.

683
00:59:37,798 --> 00:59:40,800
"I HATE YOU.
I NEVER WANT TO
SEE YOU AGAIN."

684
00:59:40,800 --> 00:59:45,805
SHE WAS EVEN MOCKING ME
FOR TAKING CARE WITH HER,
FOR USING--

685
00:59:45,805 --> 00:59:48,307
LIKE ONLY A WIMP
WOULD THINK AHEAD
LIKE THAT.

686
00:59:48,808 --> 00:59:50,810
I SAID,
"THAT'S IT. LET'S GO.

687
00:59:51,311 --> 00:59:55,314
"YOU CAN HAVE YOUR BABY
OR NOT; YOU CAN STAY WITH
YOUR CAVEMAN OR NOT.

688
00:59:55,314 --> 00:59:57,316
I DON'T CARE."

689
00:59:57,316 --> 01:00:00,821
SO THEN SHE GOT
ALL SORT OF--
[ Shifting Gears ]

690
01:00:00,821 --> 01:00:02,822
JAKE, WAIT.

691
01:00:02,822 --> 01:00:04,824
DON'T GO YET.

692
01:00:04,824 --> 01:00:07,828
[ Horn Honking ]

693
01:00:09,328 --> 01:00:11,330
NEED ANY HELP?

694
01:00:11,330 --> 01:00:13,332
WE'RE ALL RIGHT!

695
01:00:19,338 --> 01:00:21,340
LOOK--
[ Sniffles ]

696
01:00:21,340 --> 01:00:23,343
[ Sighs ]

697
01:00:23,343 --> 01:00:25,344
I DIDN'T MEAN
WHAT I SAID.

698
01:00:26,345 --> 01:00:29,850
I'M SORRY.
I REALLY AM.

699
01:00:33,352 --> 01:00:34,854
COME HERE,
I'LL SHOW YOU.

700
01:00:44,363 --> 01:00:48,367
[ Jacob ]
WE STAYED FOR
A WHILE LONGER.

701
01:00:48,367 --> 01:00:51,370
[ Sighs ]
WE SORT OF MADE UP AND...

702
01:00:51,370 --> 01:00:53,373
IT WAS NICE, BUT...

703
01:00:54,874 --> 01:00:58,377
BY NOW WE WERE BOTH
SO TIRED,

704
01:00:58,878 --> 01:01:00,380
SO WIPED OUT.

705
01:01:00,881 --> 01:01:04,383
IT WAS BEGINNING TO GET LATE,
SO I FINALLY STARTED UP THE CAR.
[ Engine Revving ]

706
01:01:08,889 --> 01:01:10,890
AND THAT WAS THAT.

707
01:01:14,894 --> 01:01:17,897
TRIED ROCKING IT,
PUSHING IT.
[ Door Closes ]

708
01:01:17,897 --> 01:01:22,902
FIRST ME, THEN BOTH OF US.
WE EVEN TRIED PUTTING
FLOOR MATS UNDER THE WHEELS.

709
01:01:22,902 --> 01:01:25,905
WE JUST ENDED UP
DIGGING OURSELVES IN DEEPER.

710
01:01:25,905 --> 01:01:28,908
SO FINALLY SHE SAYS,
"GET THE JACK.

711
01:01:28,908 --> 01:01:31,912
PACK SOME SNOW
UNDER THE RUTS
AND JACK IT UP."

712
01:01:31,912 --> 01:01:35,414
- AND THAT DIDN'T EVEN WORK.
- THIS IS THE REASON
I CAN'T BE WITH YOU.

713
01:01:35,414 --> 01:01:39,920
[ Jacob ] NOW WE'RE BOTH
REALLY PISSED OFF AGAIN.
YOU LET SHIT LIKE THIS HAPPEN.

714
01:01:39,920 --> 01:01:41,921
JUST SHUT UP,
ALL RIGHT?

715
01:01:41,921 --> 01:01:45,424
IF I WERE WITH KEVIN OR MATT,
I'D BE HOME BY NOW.
WHY ARE YOU SUCH A--

716
01:01:45,925 --> 01:01:49,428
- I SAID, SHUT UP,
ALL RIGHT?
- [ Sighs ] RICH KID.

717
01:01:49,428 --> 01:01:52,932
- FUCKIN' PUSSY.
PUSSY RICH--
- I SAID, SHUT UP!

718
01:01:55,434 --> 01:01:56,936
I DID IT.

719
01:02:00,940 --> 01:02:02,442
I SLAPPED HER.

720
01:02:05,444 --> 01:02:06,946
I JUST LOST IT.

721
01:02:17,958 --> 01:02:20,960
[ Sighs ]
DO I HAVE TO DO THIS?
PLEASE?

722
01:02:21,460 --> 01:02:24,464
YES. YOU HAVE TO.

723
01:02:27,967 --> 01:02:29,468
SHE STILL HAD
THE CROWBAR.

724
01:02:29,969 --> 01:02:31,470
YOU--
[ Grunting ]

725
01:02:40,480 --> 01:02:44,483
SHE JUST MISSED ME
BY ONE INCH, I SWEAR.
JUST ONE INCH.

726
01:02:46,986 --> 01:02:50,489
[ Both Grunting ]

727
01:02:53,993 --> 01:02:55,996
OHH!

728
01:02:56,495 --> 01:02:57,997
[ Metal Clanks ]

729
01:02:58,497 --> 01:02:59,999
[ Panting ]

730
01:03:04,503 --> 01:03:07,506
JUST THAT ONE WORD--
MURDER.

731
01:03:07,506 --> 01:03:10,510
THAT SOUNDS SO IMPOSSIBLE
TO IMAGINE.

732
01:03:14,513 --> 01:03:17,516
IT WASN'T EVEN SOMETHING
I WAS TRYING TO DO.

733
01:03:17,516 --> 01:03:20,519
IT--
IT WASN'T EVEN ME.

734
01:03:22,021 --> 01:03:26,026
IF I HAD
JUST MISSED HER
BY ONE INCH--

735
01:03:27,526 --> 01:03:29,028
ONE INCH,
JUST LIKE,

736
01:03:31,030 --> 01:03:33,032
LIKE SHE DID ME--

737
01:03:34,034 --> 01:03:36,535
[ Sighs ]
MY BIGGEST PROBLEM
WOULD BE,

738
01:03:36,535 --> 01:03:40,539
DO I SAY HELLO TO HER
WHEN I SEE HER
IN THE SCHOOL HALL.

739
01:03:51,550 --> 01:03:53,552
DARLING.

740
01:03:55,554 --> 01:03:57,057
THANKS.

741
01:03:58,557 --> 01:04:00,559
MMM.

742
01:04:00,559 --> 01:04:02,561
NOW WE KNOW.

743
01:04:02,561 --> 01:04:05,564
AT LEAST THAT'S
SOMETHING, BEN.

744
01:04:05,564 --> 01:04:10,069
IF HE TELLS IT THAT WAY
IN COURT, THE SAME WAY
HE TOLD IT TO US--

745
01:04:10,069 --> 01:04:14,073
HE WOULDN'T BE TELLING IT
TO PEOPLE WHO LOVE HIM.
NO, THEY'LL BELIEVE HIM.

746
01:04:14,073 --> 01:04:17,076
THEY'LL SEE THAT IT WAS
JUST AN ACCIDENT.

747
01:04:18,077 --> 01:04:21,080
ARE YOU PREPARED
TO BET HIS FREEDOM
ON THAT?

748
01:04:22,581 --> 01:04:26,085
WHAT'S THE ANSWER, THEN?
OF COURSE HE HAS TO TELL THEM.

749
01:04:28,087 --> 01:04:31,090
BEN, OF COURSE
HE HAS TO TELL THEM.

750
01:04:31,090 --> 01:04:33,592
LET HIM TELL PANOS
FIRST, OKAY?

751
01:04:33,592 --> 01:04:37,096
WE'RE NOT LAWYERS, CAROLYN.
THERE MIGHT BE A CERTAIN WAY
THIS SHOULD BE,

752
01:04:37,096 --> 01:04:39,098
I DON'T KNOW,
PRESENTED.

753
01:04:40,099 --> 01:04:43,103
I'LL TAKE HIM IN
TOMORROW MORNING.
OKAY?

754
01:05:22,675 --> 01:05:25,678
- YOU'RE UP PRETTY EARLY.
- [ Gasps ]

755
01:05:25,678 --> 01:05:27,680
I WASN'T GOING
ANYWHERE.

756
01:05:31,684 --> 01:05:34,186
THEY KEPT THE CAR.

757
01:05:39,692 --> 01:05:41,694
BUT IT'S CLEAN.

758
01:05:41,694 --> 01:05:43,697
AT LEAST
I HOPE TO GOD.

759
01:05:54,707 --> 01:05:58,712
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
MOM SAID SOMETHING TOO,
LAST NIGHT.

760
01:05:58,712 --> 01:06:03,215
OH, JAKE,
IT'S NOT IMPORTANT,
ALL THAT STUFF.

761
01:06:04,216 --> 01:06:07,219
TRUST ME.
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM ANYMORE.

762
01:06:07,219 --> 01:06:11,223
[ Sighs ]
DAD, YOU COULD
GO TO JAIL TOO.

763
01:06:11,223 --> 01:06:14,227
IF THEY HAVE
TO TAKE ONE OF US,
IT'S BETTER IT'S ME.

764
01:06:14,227 --> 01:06:15,728
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

765
01:06:17,730 --> 01:06:20,232
JACOB, LISTEN TO ME.

766
01:06:20,733 --> 01:06:24,737
THAT NIGHT WHEN I CAME OUT HERE
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
I WAS DOING-- PURE INSTINCT.

767
01:06:26,238 --> 01:06:29,241
BUT MAYBE I BOUGHT US
A CHANCE.

768
01:06:29,241 --> 01:06:33,245
THEY'VE GOT NO MURDER WEAPON,
NO PHYSICAL EVIDENCE,
NO WITNESSES.

769
01:06:34,747 --> 01:06:36,749
AND WE NEVER HEARD
YOUR CONFESSION.

770
01:06:36,749 --> 01:06:38,751
YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

771
01:06:38,751 --> 01:06:42,254
YOU NEVER SAID IT
AND WE NEVER HEARD IT.

772
01:06:44,758 --> 01:06:48,260
JAKE, YOU'RE NOT
REQUIRED TO TESTIFY
AGAINST YOURSELF.

773
01:06:48,260 --> 01:06:50,262
NOW, THAT'S FAIR.
THAT'S LEGAL.

774
01:06:50,262 --> 01:06:52,766
THAT'S HOW
THE SYSTEM WORKS.

775
01:06:53,766 --> 01:06:57,269
SO, IF WE ALL
JUST KEEP QUIET,

776
01:06:57,269 --> 01:06:59,271
MAYBE THEY'VE GOT
NO CASE.

777
01:06:59,271 --> 01:07:01,774
MAYBE--

778
01:07:01,774 --> 01:07:05,778
MAYBE YOU'LL WALK AWAY
FROM THIS WITH SOME KIND OF
A LIFE STILL AHEAD OF YOU.

779
01:07:05,778 --> 01:07:07,781
YEAH, BUT THERE ARE
WITNESSES.

780
01:07:07,781 --> 01:07:11,283
PEOPLE SAW US PARKED THERE.
YOU'RE NOT DENYING
YOU WERE THERE.

781
01:07:11,283 --> 01:07:13,786
YOU WERE STUCK
IN THE SNOW, RIGHT?

782
01:07:13,786 --> 01:07:16,789
YOU HAD THAT ARGUMENT
AND YOU WALKED AWAY MAD,

783
01:07:16,789 --> 01:07:19,291
LEFT HER WITH
THE CAR AND THE KEYS.

784
01:07:19,291 --> 01:07:23,296
SO YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT
THE HELL HAPPENED WHEN SHE
WAS ALONE, AND NEITHER DO WE.

785
01:07:23,296 --> 01:07:26,799
- WAIT A MINUTE.
BUT THE CAR WAS HERE.
- YOU RECONSIDERED.

786
01:07:26,799 --> 01:07:29,802
YOU CAME BACK
AND YOU FOUND HER.

787
01:07:29,802 --> 01:07:31,804
YOU JUST PANICKED.

788
01:07:31,804 --> 01:07:35,307
ISN'T THAT POSSIBLE?
BECAUSE YOU KNEW
YOU'D BE A SUSPECT.

789
01:07:35,307 --> 01:07:38,811
DROVE BACK HERE,
STILL IN A STATE OF SHOCK,
AND TOOK OFF FOR BOSTON.

790
01:07:38,811 --> 01:07:40,813
FOOLISH, YES.

791
01:07:40,813 --> 01:07:42,815
BUT NOT MURDER.

792
01:07:45,317 --> 01:07:47,820
I WISH THERE WAS
SOME OTHER WAY.

793
01:07:47,820 --> 01:07:51,824
I STAYED UP ALL NIGHT
WRACKING MY BRAINS-- ANY
OTHER WAY THAT MIGHT BE SAFE.

794
01:07:58,330 --> 01:08:00,833
IF I JUST TOLD THE TRUTH--

795
01:08:01,334 --> 01:08:05,838
THE FACT THAT YOU RAN AWAY,
NEVER WENT FOR HELP,
NEVER CAME FORWARD AT ALL--

796
01:08:05,838 --> 01:08:08,841
JAKE, HOW'S THAT
GONNA LOOK?

797
01:08:10,843 --> 01:08:14,346
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
CONVINCE A JURY.
THAT'S UP TO PANOS.

798
01:08:14,346 --> 01:08:17,850
AND LET THE PROSECUTION
TAKE THEIR SHOTS.

799
01:08:17,850 --> 01:08:21,353
ALL I'M SAYING IS,
LET'S JUST...

800
01:08:21,854 --> 01:08:23,856
NOT MAKE THEIR CASE
FOR THEM.

801
01:08:26,859 --> 01:08:31,363
SO I THOUGHT--
I FIGURED SINCE THE POLICE
WERE BOUND TO SUSPECT ME,

802
01:08:31,363 --> 01:08:34,366
THEY'D ALSO BE LOOKING
FOR THE CAR, SO...

803
01:08:35,868 --> 01:08:37,870
I THOUGHT
I'D BETTER HITCHHIKE.

804
01:08:40,372 --> 01:08:42,374
[ Clears Throat ]

805
01:08:44,877 --> 01:08:50,382
[ Sighs ]
I-I KNOW THAT WAS REALLY
STUPID AND DUMB OF ME, BUT--

806
01:08:50,382 --> 01:08:52,384
[ Sighs ]

807
01:08:53,886 --> 01:08:58,390
YOU KNOW, ALL OF IT
IS JUST A BLUR,
MR. DEMERIS.

808
01:08:58,390 --> 01:09:01,894
EVERYTHING
AFTER I WALKED BACK
AND FOUND HER THERE.

809
01:09:05,898 --> 01:09:07,900
[ Tape Recorder
Clicks Off ]

810
01:09:10,402 --> 01:09:14,907
WELL, JACOB, WHAT IF I SAID
IT SEEMED PRETTY CLEAR TO ME
THAT YOU DID IT?

811
01:09:14,907 --> 01:09:18,410
YOU HIT HER ON THE HEAD
WITH SOMETHING,
THEN YOU JUST TOOK OFF.

812
01:09:18,410 --> 01:09:20,913
- BUT I DIDN'T!
- NO, NO, NO.

813
01:09:20,913 --> 01:09:25,918
NO, I'M THE PROSECUTION NOW,
AND YOU'RE THE GUY
WHO SMASHED HER UP.

814
01:09:25,918 --> 01:09:29,922
HOW YOU GONNA PROVE TO ME
YOU DIDN'T DO IT?

815
01:09:32,925 --> 01:09:34,927
WELL, I--
NO, NO, NO, NO.

816
01:09:35,928 --> 01:09:37,930
YOU DON'T ANSWER THAT.

817
01:09:37,930 --> 01:09:41,934
NOW, REMEMBER, JACOB,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
ANSWER THAT QUESTION.

818
01:09:41,934 --> 01:09:45,437
THEYHAVE TO ANSWER IT.
THEY HAVE TO PROVE
SOMETHING ONYOU.

819
01:09:45,437 --> 01:09:48,440
YOU DO NOT HAVE TO PROVE
THE OPPOSITE.

820
01:09:50,943 --> 01:09:52,945
SO?
HOW DOES IT LOOK?

821
01:09:53,445 --> 01:09:57,950
WELL, THE GRAND JURY SITS
NEXT MONDAY, BUT WE'VE STILL
GOT A HELL OF A LOT TO PREPARE.

822
01:09:57,950 --> 01:10:00,953
- YOU MEAN THE TRIAL
STARTS MONDAY?
- NO, NO, NO.

823
01:10:00,953 --> 01:10:02,955
IT'S NOT A TRIAL.
NOT YET.

824
01:10:02,955 --> 01:10:07,960
THE GRAND JURY WEIGHS THE FACTS,
THEN DECIDES WHETHER THERE'S
ENOUGH EVIDENCE TO INDICT YOU.

825
01:10:07,960 --> 01:10:11,964
NOW, IF YOU'RE VERY,
VERY LUCKY, YOU MAY NOT
EVEN GO TO TRIAL.

826
01:10:11,964 --> 01:10:16,468
BUT I'LL HAVE A BETTER IDEA
ONCE I SEE THE FINAL
WITNESS LIST AND FORENSICS.

827
01:10:18,970 --> 01:10:20,973
THANKS.

828
01:10:20,973 --> 01:10:23,475
OKAY.
THANKS.
SEE YA.

829
01:10:23,475 --> 01:10:27,479
OH, JAKE. I'M SORRY.
I'M A LITTLE SLOW
SOMETIMES.

830
01:10:27,479 --> 01:10:30,482
I'M JUST CURIOUS.
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

831
01:10:30,482 --> 01:10:33,485
WHAT WERE THE TWO OF YOU
FIGHTING ABOUT?

832
01:10:33,485 --> 01:10:35,988
I-I MEAN,
W-WHAT GOT YOU SO MAD?

833
01:10:35,988 --> 01:10:38,991
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I LET THIS GO.

834
01:10:38,991 --> 01:10:40,993
SHE WAS PREGNANT,
FOR ONE THING.

835
01:10:42,494 --> 01:10:46,498
- I THINK YOU'D BETTER
SIT DOWN AGAIN, KIDDO.
- COME ON, SON.

836
01:10:52,004 --> 01:10:56,008
IT WAS SOMEBODY ELSE'S.
AT LEAST SHE SAID IT WAS.

837
01:10:58,010 --> 01:11:00,012
WHAT?
THIS IS GOOD?

838
01:11:00,012 --> 01:11:05,017
OH, THIS IS VERY GOOD,
MY FRIEND. THIS IS THE
BEST NEWS I'VE HEARD ALL DAY.

839
01:11:05,017 --> 01:11:08,520
AND YOU'RE CONVINCED
THAT IT COULDN'T POSSIBLY
HAVE BEEN YOURS?

840
01:11:09,521 --> 01:11:12,024
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

841
01:11:12,024 --> 01:11:14,026
YOU MEAN--

842
01:11:14,026 --> 01:11:16,528
YOU KNOW.
RIGHT. YOU KNOW.

843
01:11:18,530 --> 01:11:22,034
WELL, YEAH, BUT
WE WERE AL--
WE WERE ALWAYS--

844
01:11:22,034 --> 01:11:24,536
SAFE.
YOU CAN SAY IT, SON.
YEAH.

845
01:11:24,536 --> 01:11:27,039
AND SHE SWORE THIS
WAS SOMEBODY ELSE'S.

846
01:11:27,039 --> 01:11:31,043
GO TO THE MEDICAL EXAMINER,
GET A FULL D.N.A. REPORT.
I'M ALREADY ON IT.

847
01:11:33,045 --> 01:11:37,049
PANOS, WH-- I DON'T--
WE STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND.

848
01:11:37,049 --> 01:11:39,551
IT'S CALLED REASONABLE DOUBT,
MR. RYAN.

849
01:11:39,551 --> 01:11:43,555
SUPPOSE JACOB AND MARTHA
WERE FOLLOWED BY SOMEONE WITH
GOOD REASON TO BE JEALOUS.

850
01:11:43,555 --> 01:11:46,558
SUPPOSE THE WRONG BOYFRIEND
GOT ARRESTED.

851
01:11:50,062 --> 01:11:52,064
SO?

852
01:11:55,067 --> 01:11:57,069
SO WHAT?

853
01:11:57,069 --> 01:11:59,071
HOW DO YOU THINK
IT WENT?

854
01:12:01,073 --> 01:12:05,577
DID HE LIKE IT, YOU MEAN,
OR DIDILIKE IT?
LIKE WHAT?

855
01:12:05,577 --> 01:12:07,579
YOUR STORY.

856
01:12:07,579 --> 01:12:10,082
WELL, YES, MY STORY,
I GUESS.

857
01:12:10,082 --> 01:12:12,084
OURSTORY.

858
01:12:14,586 --> 01:12:17,089
JAKE,
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

859
01:12:17,089 --> 01:12:19,091
[ Signal Blinker
Clicking ]

860
01:12:38,610 --> 01:12:40,612
WHAT?

861
01:12:45,117 --> 01:12:47,119
REMEMBER
THAT LAST MORNING?

862
01:12:49,621 --> 01:12:53,125
THAT ARGUMENT WE HAD?
REMEMBER WHAT YOU SAID
TO ME?

863
01:12:53,125 --> 01:12:56,628
YOU SAID THAT IT'S TIME
I LEARNED TO PAY MY OWN WAY.

864
01:12:56,628 --> 01:12:58,630
AND YOU CALLED ME
A HYPOCRITE.

865
01:13:00,132 --> 01:13:04,636
JAKE, IF YOU'RE NOT
OKAY WITH THIS,
WE CAN GO BACK THERE.

866
01:13:04,636 --> 01:13:07,639
IT'S STILL
NOT TOO LATE.
[ Sighs ]
OH, MAN.

867
01:13:09,141 --> 01:13:12,644
YOU SURE THIS IS
THE BEST THING TO DO?

868
01:13:12,644 --> 01:13:16,148
I HAVEN'T BEEN SURE
OF ANYTHING IN MY LIFE
SINCE FEBRUARY 12,

869
01:13:16,148 --> 01:13:19,651
BUT IT'S WHAT
WE'VE GOT, SON;
IT'S WHAT WE'RE DOWN TO.

870
01:13:19,651 --> 01:13:22,153
ALL I'M PROPOSING IS
WE SAVE YOUR LIFE FIRST.

871
01:13:22,153 --> 01:13:24,656
LATER ON WE CAN WORRY
ABOUT YOUR SOUL.

872
01:13:25,157 --> 01:13:27,659
IS THAT BEING A HYPOCRITE?
I DON'T KNOW.

873
01:13:28,160 --> 01:13:30,662
BUT THE WORST THING
YOU CAN BE CALLED
IN THIS WORLD...

874
01:13:31,163 --> 01:13:33,665
IS SOMEONE WHO DIDN'T
STAND UP FOR HIS FAMILY.

875
01:13:33,665 --> 01:13:36,168
I--

876
01:13:36,168 --> 01:13:38,170
[ Sighs ]

877
01:13:38,170 --> 01:13:41,673
I REALLY AM GRATEFUL
FOR EVERYTHING YOU'RE
TRYING TO DO FOR ME.

878
01:13:41,673 --> 01:13:43,675
I--

879
01:13:45,676 --> 01:13:48,680
DAD, IAMGRATEFUL,
OKAY?

880
01:13:49,681 --> 01:13:51,683
I REALLY MEAN IT.

881
01:13:53,184 --> 01:13:54,686
COME ON.

882
01:13:57,689 --> 01:14:01,693
WITHOUT A WORD, BEN?
NOT ONE WORD?

883
01:14:01,693 --> 01:14:04,196
IT'S JACOB'S CHOICE,
JACOB'S LIFE.

884
01:14:06,698 --> 01:14:09,201
AND YOU HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

885
01:14:09,201 --> 01:14:11,203
WE DISCUSSED
HIS OPTIONS, YEAH.

886
01:14:11,203 --> 01:14:13,205
"OPTIONS"?

887
01:14:14,206 --> 01:14:16,207
BEN, HE'S YOUR BOY.

888
01:14:16,207 --> 01:14:19,711
HE'S SCARED AND AFRAID
AND HE WOULD DO ANYTHING
RIGHT NOW,

889
01:14:19,711 --> 01:14:23,214
HE WOULD SAY ANYTHING,
IF HE THOUGHT HE COULD
WIN BACK YOUR APPROVAL.

890
01:14:23,214 --> 01:14:25,217
HE NEVER LOST IT.

891
01:14:25,217 --> 01:14:29,221
AND IF YOU DON'T KNOW HE
DESERVES YOURS TOO, THEN YOU'VE
GOT A SERIOUS GODDAMN PROBLEM.

892
01:14:29,221 --> 01:14:31,222
HOW DARE YOU?
HOW DARE YOU?

893
01:14:31,222 --> 01:14:35,727
- IT'S DONE, IT'S TAKEN CARE OF.
- JUST LIKE YOU TOOK CARE
OF THE EVIDENCE.

894
01:14:35,727 --> 01:14:38,230
[ Ben ] THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU NEVER EVEN HAD TO
DIRTY YOUR PRECIOUS HANDS.

895
01:14:38,230 --> 01:14:40,732
[ Carolyn ]
TRIM A LITTLE HERE,
ADD A LITTLE THERE.

896
01:14:40,732 --> 01:14:44,736
HOW COULD I FORGET HOW CLEVER
YOU ARE AT MAKING THINGS?
ONE OF US HAD TO DO SOMETHING.

897
01:14:44,736 --> 01:14:47,739
DO YOU THINK YOU'VE MADE IT
EASIER ON HIM NOW?

898
01:14:47,739 --> 01:14:50,742
DO YOU NOT SEE THAT YOU
HAVE TIED HIS HANDS?

899
01:14:51,243 --> 01:14:55,247
NOW HE HAS YOU TO DEFEND
AS WELL AS HIMSELF.

900
01:14:55,747 --> 01:14:57,249
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
WHAT?

901
01:14:57,749 --> 01:15:00,752
THAT HE SHOULD PAY
WITH THE NEXT 20 YEARS,
30 YEARS OF HIS LIFE...

902
01:15:01,252 --> 01:15:02,754
FOR ONE MISTAKE,
FOR ONE MOMENT?

903
01:15:03,255 --> 01:15:06,758
THAT HE SHOULD COME OUT
OF PRISON A MIDDLE-AGED MAN?

904
01:15:07,259 --> 01:15:09,760
WHO DOES THAT BENEFIT?
WHO?

905
01:15:11,763 --> 01:15:13,265
OH, LOVE.

906
01:15:13,765 --> 01:15:16,767
SOONER OR LATER SOMEBODY'S
GONNA HAVE TO BE FORGIVEN--

907
01:15:16,767 --> 01:15:20,772
HIM FOR WHAT HE DID, OR US
BECAUSE WE DID NOTHING WHEN
WE HAD A CHANCE TO SAVE HIM.

908
01:15:25,777 --> 01:15:27,779
WOULDN'T YOU RATHER
FORGIVE HIM?

909
01:15:35,787 --> 01:15:38,790
[ Whispers ]
HEY... JUDE.

910
01:15:44,796 --> 01:15:46,798
[ Door Closes ]

911
01:15:52,804 --> 01:15:54,805
[ People Murmuring,
Chattering ]

912
01:16:08,320 --> 01:16:10,321
GOOD NEWS.

913
01:16:10,321 --> 01:16:14,826
OKAY, I STOPPED AT THE LAB
ON THE WAY UP HERE.

914
01:16:14,826 --> 01:16:18,829
NOW, THEY HAD THE M.E.'S
FETAL TISSUE ANALYSIS...

915
01:16:18,829 --> 01:16:22,834
AND THEY HAVE
THAT BLOOD SAMPLE THAT
WE SUBMITTED FROM JACOB.

916
01:16:22,834 --> 01:16:25,336
OKAY, THIS GETS
PRETTY TECHNICAL, BUT--

917
01:16:25,336 --> 01:16:27,339
JACOB WASN'T
THE FATHER.

918
01:16:27,339 --> 01:16:29,341
BINGO.

919
01:16:29,341 --> 01:16:32,344
OH, MAN, LISTEN TO ME,
TELLING A DOCTOR
WHAT'S TECHNICAL.

920
01:16:32,344 --> 01:16:34,846
BUT THIS WORKS
BOTH WAYS, DOESN'T IT?

921
01:16:34,846 --> 01:16:38,350
I MEAN, THEY COULD SAY
HE WAS JEALOUS.
THIS GIVES HIM A MOTIVE.

922
01:16:38,350 --> 01:16:41,852
THIS LETS US
GO AFTER THE GIRL,
ATTACK HER CHARACTER.

923
01:16:41,852 --> 01:16:45,357
MARTHA TAVERNER JUST BLEW
50 SYMPATHY POINTS.

924
01:16:45,357 --> 01:16:48,859
LOOK AT IT THIS WAY:
THIS INTRODUCES DOUBT.

925
01:16:48,859 --> 01:16:51,863
AND DOUBT, KIDDO,
IS OUR VERY BEST FRIEND.

926
01:16:51,863 --> 01:16:54,866
- [ Door Opens ]
- MRS. RYAN?

927
01:16:54,866 --> 01:16:57,369
[ Ben Shouting ]
GET AWAY FROM ME!
EXCUSE ME. MRS. RYAN.

928
01:16:57,369 --> 01:17:00,372
WHAT HAPPENED?
WE'LL SEE YOU DAY AFTER
TOMORROW AT 10:00.

929
01:17:00,372 --> 01:17:02,374
YES, THAT'S FINE.
[ Reporters Shouting ]

930
01:17:02,874 --> 01:17:06,378
BENNY? BEN?
SCREW THEM! FORGET
THE WHOLE BUNCH OF THEM!

931
01:17:06,378 --> 01:17:09,381
I DIDN'T TESTIFY
AND I WON'T TESTIFY!

932
01:17:09,381 --> 01:17:13,385
SO YOU CAN PRINT
ANY DAMN THING YOU WANT TO!
HERE, GET THIS ONE!

933
01:17:13,385 --> 01:17:16,888
YOU DIDN'T TESTIFY?
THERE'S GOTTA BE SOME
PROTECTION, SOME IMMUNITY,

934
01:17:16,888 --> 01:17:20,892
SOME KIND OF PRIVILEGE SO THEY
CAN'T TRY TO MAKE YOU SNITCH
ON YOUR OWN FLESH AND BLOOD.

935
01:17:20,892 --> 01:17:24,396
WHY DON'T YOU WRITE THAT?
THERE'S SUCH A THING AS
THE FIFTH AMENDMENT.

936
01:17:24,396 --> 01:17:26,897
ASK MY LAWYER!
[ Reporter Shouting ]
WHAT ARE YOU HIDING?

937
01:17:27,398 --> 01:17:30,402
WEREN'T YOU
LISTENING TO ME?

938
01:17:30,402 --> 01:17:34,405
I TOLD YOU IF YOU HAD ANYTHING
TO ASK, COME OUT AND ASK ME!
I DIDN'T HAVE ANY QUESTIONS.

939
01:17:34,405 --> 01:17:37,909
FIND ME SOME PRIVILEGE.
"FIND ME SOME PRIVILEGE."
WHAT, MAKE SOMETHING UP?

940
01:17:37,909 --> 01:17:40,912
[ Reporters Murmuring ]
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS PARENT-CHILD IMMUNITY.

941
01:17:40,912 --> 01:17:43,915
THERE OUGHTA BE.
YOU KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE ASKING FOR?

942
01:17:43,915 --> 01:17:46,918
YOU'RE ASKING TO GO
TO JAIL FOR CONTEMPT,
FOR STARTERS.

943
01:17:46,918 --> 01:17:50,421
YOU'RE ASKING ME TO GO
TO JAIL TOO, AND I'M NOT
DOING ANY SUCH THING FOR YOU.

944
01:17:50,421 --> 01:17:52,424
WHAT DID HE MEAN
BY "PRIVILEGE"?

945
01:17:53,925 --> 01:17:56,927
YOU'RE ACTING
AS IF WE'VE GOT SOMETHING
TO HIDE ABOUT JACOB.

946
01:17:56,927 --> 01:18:01,433
THEY TWISTED EVERY WORD I SAID,
TRIED TO TRICK ME INTO SOME
KIND OF CONFLICTING EVIDENCE.

947
01:18:01,433 --> 01:18:05,436
I WON'T PLAY THAT GAME.
I TOLD THEM SO. I GAVE THEM
A STATEMENT OF PRINCIPLE.

948
01:18:05,436 --> 01:18:08,940
AND WHAT WAS THAT PRINCIPLE?
I THINK I MISSED THAT PART.
I DON'T BARGAIN FOR MY SON.

949
01:18:08,940 --> 01:18:12,443
AND I WON'T HELP THEM
TO CONVICT HIM.
JESUS, BEN!

950
01:18:12,443 --> 01:18:15,947
I WON'T TESTIFY, PANOS.
NOT TODAY, NOT EVER.

951
01:18:15,947 --> 01:18:18,950
IF I HAVE TO GO TO JAIL,
SO BE IT.

952
01:18:18,950 --> 01:18:22,954
AND IF THERE WAS ANY MORE
I COULD DO, YOU'D BETTER
BELIEVE I'D DO THAT TOO.

953
01:18:22,954 --> 01:18:24,956
[ Reporters Shouting ]

954
01:18:24,956 --> 01:18:26,958
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

955
01:18:35,265 --> 01:18:37,135
[ Knock On Door ]

956
01:18:37,135 --> 01:18:40,138
OH. GIVE ME A MINUTE,
BEN, PLEASE.

957
01:18:43,140 --> 01:18:45,143
MOM, CAN I
TALK TO YOU?

958
01:18:47,645 --> 01:18:49,647
MM-HMM.

959
01:18:54,152 --> 01:18:56,654
MOM, THEY'RE LYING.

960
01:18:56,654 --> 01:19:00,158
THEY'RE COMPLETELY CHANGING
THE TRUTH OF WHAT HAPPENED.

961
01:19:00,158 --> 01:19:03,161
HOW CAN YOU
LET THEM DO THAT?

962
01:19:04,162 --> 01:19:08,166
WELL, PEOPLE DON'T GO
TO COURT NECESSARILY...

963
01:19:08,166 --> 01:19:11,169
TO TELL THE TRUTH ABOUT
EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED.

964
01:19:12,670 --> 01:19:16,674
THEY, UM-- THEY GO
TO DEFEND THEMSELVES
THE BEST WAY THEY CAN.

965
01:19:17,175 --> 01:19:20,178
BUT YOU HEARD JACOB
AND YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

966
01:19:21,678 --> 01:19:24,682
ARE YOU JUST GONNA DO
WHAT DADDY SAYS?

967
01:19:24,682 --> 01:19:26,684
[ Sighs ]
JUDE.

968
01:19:26,684 --> 01:19:31,189
DIDN'T YOU EVER LEARN
SOMETHING ABOUT A FRIEND
OF YOURS, SOME SECRET,

969
01:19:31,189 --> 01:19:36,193
BUT YOU KNEW IF YOU TOLD HER
IT WOULD JUST HURT HER FEELINGS,
SO YOU DIDN'T TELL?

970
01:19:36,693 --> 01:19:39,197
I MEAN, THAT'S NOT--

971
01:19:39,197 --> 01:19:41,199
THAT'S NOT LYING EXACTLY.

972
01:19:41,199 --> 01:19:44,201
IT'S-- YOU JUST DIDN'T
VOLUNTEER SOMETHING.

973
01:19:44,201 --> 01:19:46,204
JUST BECAUSE
THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE DO,

974
01:19:46,204 --> 01:19:50,708
JUST BECAUSE THEY MIGHT
GET AWAY WITH IT, DOES THAT
MEAN YOU HAVE TO LIE?

975
01:19:52,209 --> 01:19:54,212
SOMETIMES-- YOU'RE JUST--
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG...

976
01:19:54,212 --> 01:19:56,214
TO UNDERSTAND SOME THINGS,
THAT'S ALL.

977
01:19:56,214 --> 01:20:00,217
I'M JUST BEGINNING TO LEARN
SOME OF THEM MYSELF.

978
01:20:00,217 --> 01:20:03,221
SOMEDAY, DARLING,
YOU MIGHT...
DON'T TELL ME "SOMEDAY"!

979
01:20:03,221 --> 01:20:06,723
UNDERSTAND WHAT DADDY--
I CAN'T STAND IT
WHEN YOU SAY "SOMEDAY"!

980
01:20:06,723 --> 01:20:09,227
THIS IS HAPPENING
TO ME RIGHT NOW.

981
01:20:09,227 --> 01:20:12,230
[ Judith ]
YOU LET DADDY CONVINCE YOU.

982
01:20:12,230 --> 01:20:15,232
IT'S DISGUSTING.

983
01:20:15,232 --> 01:20:19,237
NOBODY EVEN CARES
WHAT I THINK; I'M JUST
A STUPID LITTLE KID.

984
01:20:20,738 --> 01:20:24,242
NOBODY EVEN THINKS THAT
I COULD GO AND TELL.

985
01:20:24,242 --> 01:20:26,244
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"TELL"?

986
01:20:26,244 --> 01:20:28,746
YOU FIGURE IT OUT!
JUDITH.

987
01:20:28,746 --> 01:20:31,749
[ Door Slams ]
[ Footsteps
Descending Stairs ]

988
01:20:34,752 --> 01:20:38,255
CAROLYN,
YOU ASLEEP?

989
01:20:38,255 --> 01:20:40,258
MM-MMM.

990
01:20:41,759 --> 01:20:44,761
ABRAHAM AND ISAAC.
REMEMBER THAT STORY?

991
01:20:47,265 --> 01:20:49,267
GOD SAYS TO ABRAHAM,

992
01:20:49,767 --> 01:20:51,769
"PROVE YOUR FAITH.

993
01:20:51,769 --> 01:20:55,273
"TAKE ISAAC,
YOUR BELOVED SON,
AND SACRIFICE HIM.

994
01:20:57,275 --> 01:20:59,277
"WHY?
BECAUSE I'M GOD.

995
01:20:59,277 --> 01:21:01,278
BECAUSE I SAY SO."

996
01:21:02,280 --> 01:21:04,282
AND ABRAHAM IS WILLING.

997
01:21:04,282 --> 01:21:06,784
HE'S VERY SAD,
BUT HE'LL DO IT.

998
01:21:06,784 --> 01:21:08,785
HE'LL CUT
HIS OWN SON'S THROAT...

999
01:21:08,785 --> 01:21:10,788
IF THAT'S WHAT GOD
REQUIRES.

1000
01:21:12,290 --> 01:21:14,792
VERY OBEDIENT,
ABRAHAM.

1001
01:21:14,792 --> 01:21:16,793
AND VERY RIGHTEOUS.

1002
01:21:19,297 --> 01:21:23,300
BUT WHEN
THEY TELL THAT STORY
THEY ALWAYS MISS THE POINT.

1003
01:21:25,303 --> 01:21:27,305
WHO'D WANT HIM
FOR A FATHER?

1004
01:21:39,316 --> 01:21:41,319
[ People Chattering
Quietly ]

1005
01:22:02,339 --> 01:22:04,342
GOOD MORNING, CAROLYN.
HI.

1006
01:22:06,344 --> 01:22:10,347
FIRST TIME
YOU'VE DONATED BLOOD?
YES.

1007
01:22:10,347 --> 01:22:12,350
[ Sighs ]

1008
01:22:14,852 --> 01:22:16,853
[ Toilet Flushes ]

1009
01:22:32,369 --> 01:22:34,372
MRS. TAVERNER.

1010
01:22:36,374 --> 01:22:38,376
OH, PLEASE.

1011
01:22:43,881 --> 01:22:47,884
THIS HAS BEEN,
FOR ME, FOR ALL OF US--
IT'S THE HARDEST--

1012
01:22:47,884 --> 01:22:52,390
I'VE JUST-- I'VE SPENT
A THOUSAND HOURS NOT SLEEPING,

1013
01:22:52,390 --> 01:22:55,892
THINKING ABOUT... MARTHA.

1014
01:22:56,393 --> 01:22:59,397
AND I JUST WANT YOU
TO KNOW HOW SORRY I AM.

1015
01:22:59,397 --> 01:23:02,899
I AM SO SORRY.

1016
01:23:05,903 --> 01:23:08,406
I KNOW IT WON'T
CHANGE ANYTHING, BUT--

1017
01:23:08,906 --> 01:23:11,408
[ Sighs ]
OH, GOD, IF YOU COULD--

1018
01:23:11,908 --> 01:23:13,911
WHAT?
IF I COULD WHAT?

1019
01:23:13,911 --> 01:23:16,914
IF YOU COULD SOMEHOW...

1020
01:23:16,914 --> 01:23:20,918
LOOK AT US AS HUMAN--
AS A FAMILY, I MEAN.

1021
01:23:20,918 --> 01:23:24,422
JUST AS A FAMILY
THAT'S ALSO SO HELPLESS.

1022
01:23:25,922 --> 01:23:30,928
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
TO BE HELPLESS ABOUT?
YOU TELL ME THAT.

1023
01:23:30,928 --> 01:23:33,930
SHE WAS ALIVE IN THE MORNING
WHEN I SAID GOOD-BYE TO HER.

1024
01:23:33,930 --> 01:23:37,435
YOU'RE A DOCTOR.
YOU THINK ABOUT THIS,
WHERE SHE IS NOW.

1025
01:23:37,435 --> 01:23:39,937
AND NOTHING YOU SAY
IS GONNA GET ANY PITY
OUT OF ME.

1026
01:23:39,937 --> 01:23:42,939
OH, I'M NOT ASKING
FOR YOUR PITY.

1027
01:23:42,939 --> 01:23:46,944
I'M-- I'M JUST--
YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET HIM OFF.

1028
01:23:46,944 --> 01:23:49,446
WITH YOUR BIG SHOT LAWYER
AND ALL YOUR MONEY.

1029
01:23:49,446 --> 01:23:52,950
HE'S FREE TO WALK THE STREETS
RIGHT NOW, AND YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET HIM OFF.

1030
01:23:52,950 --> 01:23:56,953
PEOPLE LIKE YOU THINK
THEY OWN THE WORLD.

1031
01:23:56,953 --> 01:23:59,457
[ People Chattering ]

1032
01:24:13,470 --> 01:24:15,973
[ Glass Breaking ]

1033
01:24:15,973 --> 01:24:17,975
JESUS.

1034
01:24:25,483 --> 01:24:27,484
- STAY INSIDE.
CALL THE POLICE.
- [ Carolyn ] NO, BEN!

1035
01:24:27,984 --> 01:24:29,987
- [ Jacob ] DAD, DON'T!
- [ Ben ] HEY!

1036
01:24:30,488 --> 01:24:34,491
- COME HERE, YOU BASTARD!
- [ Man ] I DID IT.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

1037
01:24:34,991 --> 01:24:36,994
- BEN!
- [ Man Grunts ]

1038
01:24:42,999 --> 01:24:46,003
HEY! HEY, YOU!
COME ON!
JAKE! JAKE!

1039
01:24:46,003 --> 01:24:49,005
PLEASE!
LET'S GO!
COME ON!

1040
01:24:49,506 --> 01:24:53,010
[ Men Yelling,
Whooping ]

1041
01:25:00,017 --> 01:25:03,020
MOM!
GOD!

1042
01:25:03,020 --> 01:25:05,021
GODDAMN IT!

1043
01:25:05,021 --> 01:25:07,023
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
YEAH.

1044
01:25:07,023 --> 01:25:11,528
HERE!
THIS IS YOUR FAULT!
BOTH OF YOURS!

1045
01:25:11,528 --> 01:25:14,531
YOU'VE TURNED US ALL
INTO FREAKS!
SHUT UP, ALL RIGHT?

1046
01:25:14,531 --> 01:25:17,535
I WISH YOU'D NEVER COME BACK.
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST STAY AWAY?

1047
01:25:19,036 --> 01:25:21,538
I HATE YOU!
I HATE YOU!

1048
01:25:21,538 --> 01:25:24,041
OHH!
[ Ben ]
IT'S OKAY, JAKE.

1049
01:25:24,041 --> 01:25:26,043
[ Yells ]

1050
01:25:26,043 --> 01:25:28,044
AAAH! GOD!

1051
01:25:28,044 --> 01:25:30,046
HELP!
[ Carolyn ]
JACOB!

1052
01:25:30,046 --> 01:25:33,050
[ Ben ]
GET DOWN!
[ Jacob Whimpering ]

1053
01:25:33,551 --> 01:25:36,052
[ Crying ]
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

1054
01:25:36,052 --> 01:25:38,556
LET'S GENTLY, GENTLY
GET HIM UP.

1055
01:25:38,556 --> 01:25:41,559
IT'S OKAY.
COME ON, SWEETHEART.
LET ME LOOK. LET ME SEE.

1056
01:25:42,559 --> 01:25:45,061
THAT'S IT, THAT'S IT,
THAT'S IT.

1057
01:25:45,061 --> 01:25:48,065
NO, NO. I CAN'T--
I CAN'T TREAT THIS HERE.
[ Whimpering ]

1058
01:25:48,065 --> 01:25:50,567
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
TAKE HIM TO THE OFFICE.
I'LL COME TOO.

1059
01:25:51,067 --> 01:25:53,069
NO, YOU STAY HERE
WITH JUDITH.
CAROLYN, I--

1060
01:25:53,069 --> 01:25:55,072
PLEASE, BEN.

1061
01:26:01,078 --> 01:26:03,581
THIS WON'T HURT,
I PROMISE.

1062
01:26:09,587 --> 01:26:11,088
THERE YOU GO.

1063
01:26:11,589 --> 01:26:14,090
I'M JUST GONNA
WRAP THIS UP...

1064
01:26:14,090 --> 01:26:17,595
SO WE DON'T HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT INFECTION.

1065
01:26:17,595 --> 01:26:20,097
OKAY?

1066
01:26:20,097 --> 01:26:24,101
YOU MAY START TO FEEL
DROWSY NOW FROM THAT SHOT.

1067
01:26:24,101 --> 01:26:27,104
SO IF YOU DO, YOU JUST
PUT YOUR HEAD DOWN.
OKAY, LOVE?

1068
01:26:27,104 --> 01:26:29,105
OKAY.

1069
01:26:33,110 --> 01:26:35,112
MOM?
MM-HMM?

1070
01:26:37,113 --> 01:26:39,115
JUDE IS RIGHT.

1071
01:26:40,618 --> 01:26:44,120
YOU'D ALL BE BETTER OFF
IF I JUST DISAPPEARED.

1072
01:26:44,120 --> 01:26:46,122
MAYBE I STILL SHOULD.

1073
01:26:46,122 --> 01:26:48,125
DON'T EVEN SAY THAT.

1074
01:26:51,127 --> 01:26:54,130
I DON'T MEAN JUST YOU.
I MEAN--

1075
01:26:54,632 --> 01:26:57,134
I MEAN THE WHOLE TOWN.

1076
01:26:57,635 --> 01:26:59,636
I MEAN, THAT'S WHAT
THEY WANT, ISN'T IT?

1077
01:26:59,636 --> 01:27:02,139
NO.

1078
01:27:02,640 --> 01:27:05,643
NO, JAKE, THOSE MEN--

1079
01:27:05,643 --> 01:27:08,645
THOSE MEN TONIGHT
WERE COWARDS.

1080
01:27:09,145 --> 01:27:11,148
IF YOU SAW THEM TOMORROW
IN THEIR SHOPS,

1081
01:27:11,148 --> 01:27:14,651
THEY'D SMILE AND NOD
WHILE THEY GAVE YOU CHANGE.

1082
01:27:17,655 --> 01:27:20,157
I'M THE COWARD.

1083
01:27:20,157 --> 01:27:22,158
I'M THE COWARD.

1084
01:27:26,163 --> 01:27:29,666
I FEEL LIKE I'M BEING
TORN APART, YOU KNOW?

1085
01:27:30,667 --> 01:27:33,671
AND--
[ Sighs ]

1086
01:27:33,671 --> 01:27:36,173
IF I HOLD THIS IN,
I-IT'S LIKE...

1087
01:27:39,676 --> 01:27:41,679
A POISON, YOU KNOW?

1088
01:27:41,679 --> 01:27:44,681
IF I TELL THE TRUTH,
DAD'LL GO TO JAIL TOO.

1089
01:27:44,681 --> 01:27:46,683
HE'LL HATE ME.

1090
01:27:49,186 --> 01:27:51,188
EITHER WAY,
IT'S THE END OF US.

1091
01:27:52,689 --> 01:27:55,692
YOUR DAD'LL NEVER,
NEVER HATE YOU.

1092
01:27:58,696 --> 01:28:00,697
YOUR DAD LOVES YOU...

1093
01:28:02,198 --> 01:28:04,201
SO MUCH, JACOB.

1094
01:28:09,205 --> 01:28:12,209
AND RIGHT OR WRONG,
HE ALWAYS GIVES...

1095
01:28:12,209 --> 01:28:14,211
HIS WHOLE HEART.

1096
01:28:14,211 --> 01:28:16,212
IT CAN BE PRETTY
OVERWHELMING SOMETIMES...

1097
01:28:16,212 --> 01:28:19,216
BECAUSE HE JUST ALWAYS
SEEMS SO SURE.

1098
01:28:21,218 --> 01:28:24,220
BUT YOU DON'T HAVE TO
BE THAT WAY.

1099
01:28:25,221 --> 01:28:27,725
YOU KNOW?

1100
01:28:27,725 --> 01:28:31,227
IT IS POSSIBLE
TO DISAGREE WITH SOMEONE...

1101
01:28:32,729 --> 01:28:34,231
AND STILL LOVE THEM.

1102
01:28:41,739 --> 01:28:45,241
AT A CERTAIN POINT,
WE JUST--

1103
01:28:45,241 --> 01:28:47,744
WE HAVE TO MAKE
OUR OWN DECISIONS.

1104
01:28:49,245 --> 01:28:52,749
YEAH. YEAH, BUT HE
RISKED SO MUCH FOR ME.

1105
01:28:53,249 --> 01:28:55,251
MMM.

1106
01:28:55,251 --> 01:28:57,254
HE DIDN'T EVEN STOP
TO COUNT THE PRICE.

1107
01:28:57,254 --> 01:28:59,256
HE JUST DID IT.

1108
01:29:05,262 --> 01:29:07,264
MOM?
HMM?

1109
01:29:09,265 --> 01:29:11,267
HOW CAN I LET HIM DOWN?

1110
01:29:14,772 --> 01:29:17,273
HOW CAN I
DO THAT TO HIM?

1111
01:29:18,775 --> 01:29:20,778
YEAH.

1112
01:29:22,279 --> 01:29:24,280
HOW CAN YOU?

1113
01:29:46,019 --> 01:29:48,020
[ Whispering ]

1114
01:29:48,020 --> 01:29:50,022
MRS. RYAN?

1115
01:30:03,035 --> 01:30:05,037
DR. RYAN?

1116
01:30:10,543 --> 01:30:14,047
[ People Chattering ]
THERE SHE IS!

1117
01:30:14,548 --> 01:30:16,049
DR. RYAN!
DR. RYAN, DID YOU ALSO
REFUSE TO TESTIFY?

1118
01:30:16,550 --> 01:30:19,552
- HOW'D IT GO, TROUPER?
- I DID IT. I TOLD THEM.

1119
01:30:19,552 --> 01:30:21,555
SEE?
WHAT'D I TELL YOU?

1120
01:30:21,555 --> 01:30:26,058
NO SWEAT.
NO, I MEAN I TOLD THEM
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED.

1121
01:30:26,058 --> 01:30:28,060
WHAT?

1122
01:30:28,060 --> 01:30:30,564
BEN AND JACOB
HAVEN'T BEEN TELLING YOU
THE TRUTH, PANOS.

1123
01:30:31,064 --> 01:30:34,066
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU HAVEN'T KNOWN THAT.
WHOA, WHOA!

1124
01:30:34,567 --> 01:30:36,570
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
GONNA DO ABOUT THIS.
YOU COME WITH ME.

1125
01:30:37,070 --> 01:30:38,572
[ Reporter ]
MIGHT WE HAVE
A STATEMENT, PLEASE?

1126
01:30:39,072 --> 01:30:40,573
DR. RYAN!
EXCUSE ME!

1127
01:30:44,578 --> 01:30:46,580
TALK.

1128
01:30:46,580 --> 01:30:48,581
IT'S HARD TO SAY.
THEY'VE BEEN IN THERE
20 MINUTES.

1129
01:30:49,081 --> 01:30:52,085
THERE'S NO STORY HERE.
TWENTY MINUTES!
WHAT ARE THEY TALKING ABOUT?

1130
01:30:54,087 --> 01:30:56,088
OKAY. MY TURN.

1131
01:30:56,088 --> 01:30:58,090
JACOB DOESN'T KNOW,
DOES HE?

1132
01:31:00,594 --> 01:31:02,595
DID YOU AT LEAST
TELL BEN?

1133
01:31:04,597 --> 01:31:07,099
OH, JESUS CHRIST.

1134
01:31:10,102 --> 01:31:13,606
ALL I CAN SAY IS I HOPE HE
DOESN'T HAVE HIS SON'S TEMPER,
BECAUSE I WORRY ABOUT YOU.

1135
01:31:13,606 --> 01:31:16,109
HE DOESN'T HAVE
HIS SON'S TEMPER.

1136
01:31:16,109 --> 01:31:18,611
HIS SON HAS HIS.
THIS WEAPON.

1137
01:31:18,611 --> 01:31:22,114
THIS CAR JACK
THAT YOU SAY KILLED HER.
WHERE IS IT NOW?

1138
01:31:22,114 --> 01:31:26,619
IT'LL NEVER SURFACE,
I PROMISE YOU,
BUT I'M NEVER GOING TO SAY.

1139
01:31:26,619 --> 01:31:28,621
- DID YOU EVER SEE IT?
- MM-MMM.

1140
01:31:30,123 --> 01:31:32,125
WELL, THEN IT'S HEARSAY.

1141
01:31:32,125 --> 01:31:36,128
JUST LIKE THIS SO-CALLED
CONFESSION; IT'S YOUR WORD
AGAINST BEN AND JACOB'S.

1142
01:31:36,128 --> 01:31:39,633
THERE'S STILL NO PROOF.
PANOS, IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

1143
01:31:39,633 --> 01:31:42,134
WHY CAN'T JACOB
JUST TELL THE TRUTH?

1144
01:31:42,134 --> 01:31:45,137
JACOB IS MY CLIENT,
NOT YOU, NOT YOUR HUSBAND.
JACOB.

1145
01:31:45,137 --> 01:31:47,641
AND THERE'S NO WAY
I'M GOING TO PUT HIM
ON THAT WITNESS STAND...

1146
01:31:47,641 --> 01:31:50,142
FOR MARIAN RAYNOR
TO CUT TO PIECES.

1147
01:31:50,142 --> 01:31:53,647
I'M GONNA DEFEND YOUR SON
EVEN IF YOU DON'T.

1148
01:31:56,649 --> 01:31:59,652
EVEN IF IT MEANS
HANGING YOU OUT TO DRY.

1149
01:32:00,653 --> 01:32:03,156
ME?
COLD.

1150
01:32:03,156 --> 01:32:06,158
VINDICTIVE.

1151
01:32:06,158 --> 01:32:10,163
FULL OF CRAZY, PARANOID
FANTASIES ABOUT YOUR SON
AND HIS LOW-CLASS LOVER.

1152
01:32:10,163 --> 01:32:13,666
HONEY, BY THE TIME
I'M DONE WITH YOU,
YOU'LL LOOK LIKE MEDEA.

1153
01:32:13,666 --> 01:32:17,170
PANOS, IF YOU TRY
TO GO ON HIDING THIS--

1154
01:32:17,170 --> 01:32:19,672
IF WE DON'T,
AT SOME POINT, ACCEPT
WHAT ACTUALLY DID HAPPEN--

1155
01:32:20,172 --> 01:32:24,177
WHAT ACTUALLY HAPPENED?
CAROLYN, WHAT'S IT GONNA TAKE
FOR YOU TO GET THIS?

1156
01:32:24,177 --> 01:32:27,680
THEY TELL THEIR VERSION
OF THE STORY; WE TELL OURS.

1157
01:32:28,180 --> 01:32:31,183
- AND THESE 12 PEOPLE
DECIDE THE TRUTH.
- THAT'S NOT THE TRUTH.

1158
01:32:31,183 --> 01:32:33,687
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT A CONTEST
BETWEEN AD CAMPAIGNS.

1159
01:32:33,687 --> 01:32:36,689
- I'M TALKING ABOUT
SAVING YOUR SON.
- SO AM I.

1160
01:32:38,691 --> 01:32:42,194
IT'S ABSOLUTE,
WHY I DID THIS, PANOS.

1161
01:32:42,194 --> 01:32:46,198
FINALLY, IT'S JUST
ONE TRUE THING.

1162
01:32:46,198 --> 01:32:48,702
ABSOLUTE.

1163
01:32:48,702 --> 01:32:52,204
I DIDN'T ASK YOUR PERMISSION
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANT IT.

1164
01:32:53,205 --> 01:32:54,708
WE CAN'T AFFORD IT ANYMORE.

1165
01:32:58,210 --> 01:33:00,212
OH, MY DEAR DOCTOR.

1166
01:33:02,716 --> 01:33:05,217
YOU AND YOUR
GODDAMN ABSOLUTES.

1167
01:33:05,217 --> 01:33:07,720
YOU'LL SEE WHAT
A SHALLOW, LITTLE THING
YOUR PRINCIPLES ARE...

1168
01:33:07,720 --> 01:33:10,724
WHEN YOUR FAMILY'S
BLOWN TO HELL.

1169
01:33:11,224 --> 01:33:13,726
AND YOU WON'T
BE ABLE TO TAKE BACK
ONE SINGLE WORD.

1170
01:33:18,231 --> 01:33:20,232
JACOB. JACOB.
WHAT?

1171
01:33:20,232 --> 01:33:23,235
COME ON, WAKE UP.
COME AND HEAR WHAT
YOUR MOTHER'S DONE.

1172
01:33:23,235 --> 01:33:27,240
SHE'S DONE IT NOW, BOY.
SHE JUST COULDN'T KEEP
HER BIG MOUTH SHUT.

1173
01:33:27,240 --> 01:33:29,742
DAD, STOP.
YOU'RE HURTING ME.
WHAT IS IT? WHAT'S WRONG?

1174
01:33:29,742 --> 01:33:32,244
SHE'LL TELL YOU HERSELF.

1175
01:33:32,244 --> 01:33:34,247
TELL HIM.
TELL HIM!

1176
01:33:34,247 --> 01:33:38,250
WHAT KIND OF A LIFE
ARE WE GOING TO HAVE,
HMM?

1177
01:33:39,251 --> 01:33:41,755
WHAT KIND OF A LIFE,
ALL OF US?

1178
01:33:43,255 --> 01:33:47,259
I LOVE YOU AND I WANTED
TO SAVE YOU.

1179
01:33:47,259 --> 01:33:50,262
BUT SAVE YOU FOR WHAT?
AS WHAT?

1180
01:33:50,262 --> 01:33:53,265
EVERYTHING HE'S
BEEN FOR 16 YEARS,
EVERYTHING HE IS.

1181
01:33:53,265 --> 01:33:56,269
- THAT WASN'T ENOUGH
TO MAKE HIM VALUABLE?
- OHH.

1182
01:33:56,269 --> 01:33:58,771
YOU NEVER WANTED TO SAVE HIM.
YOU BROUGHT HIM
INTO THIS LIFE...

1183
01:33:58,771 --> 01:34:01,273
- BUT YOU'RE NOT
WILLING TO FORGIVE HIM.
- I FORGIVE US ALL, BEN.

1184
01:34:01,273 --> 01:34:03,276
JAKE, FOR GOD'S SAKE,
DON'T LISTEN TO HER.

1185
01:34:03,777 --> 01:34:05,278
WE CAN'T GIVE UP NOW.
OH, LEAVE HIM ALONE.

1186
01:34:05,778 --> 01:34:08,280
THERE'S STILL A CHANCE.
DON'T YOU HAVE ANY FAITH
IN HIM AT ALL?

1187
01:34:08,280 --> 01:34:11,284
WE CAN STILL FIGHT THIS,
YOU AND ME TOGETHER.
YOU BACK OFF.

1188
01:34:11,284 --> 01:34:14,787
BACK OFF MY SON.
IF HE'S YOUR SON,
THEN ACT LIKE IT.

1189
01:34:14,787 --> 01:34:17,790
JACOB. JAKIE,
I DID THIS FOR YOU,
FOR BOTH OF YOU.

1190
01:34:17,790 --> 01:34:20,293
I ONLY WAS TRYING TO HELP YOU.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?
OH, COME ON!

1191
01:34:20,293 --> 01:34:23,796
YOU'RE ASKING A HELL OF A LOT
IF YOU EXPECT YOUR OWN SON TO
UNDERSTAND WHY YOU BETRAYED HIM.

1192
01:34:23,796 --> 01:34:26,800
- I DIDN'T BE--
YOU CAN'T SAY THAT!
- GODDAMN IT, JUST STOP IT!

1193
01:34:26,800 --> 01:34:28,801
ALL RIGHT?

1194
01:34:32,805 --> 01:34:34,808
BOTH OF YOU.

1195
01:34:44,767 --> 01:34:47,269
HEY, MOM! MOM!
WAKE UP!

1196
01:34:47,269 --> 01:34:49,773
JACOB'S GONE.
HMM?

1197
01:34:49,773 --> 01:34:51,774
WHAT?

1198
01:34:56,278 --> 01:34:59,281
JACOB! HE'S GONE.
HE'S GONE.

1199
01:35:03,786 --> 01:35:05,789
CHECK THE KITCHEN
AND THE BACK OF THE HOUSE.

1200
01:35:06,289 --> 01:35:07,790
I ALREADY LOOKED.
LOOK AGAIN.

1201
01:35:20,303 --> 01:35:22,304
OH, NO.

1202
01:35:22,304 --> 01:35:24,306
OHH.

1203
01:35:31,313 --> 01:35:34,316
THE JEEP'S GONE.
HE'S RUNNING AGAIN,
AND THIS TIME HE'LL NEVER STOP.

1204
01:35:34,316 --> 01:35:37,820
NO, HE DIDN'T TAKE
ANY CLOTHES OR FOOD.
I'M ALMOST SURE, BEN.

1205
01:35:37,820 --> 01:35:40,322
MAYBE HE DOESN'T THINK
HE'LL NEED THEM.

1206
01:35:40,322 --> 01:35:44,327
MAYBE HE'S GONNA
DRIVE THAT THING
STRAIGHT INTO A TREE.

1207
01:35:44,327 --> 01:35:47,329
OH, MY GOD.

1208
01:35:47,329 --> 01:35:49,832
NO, THAT CAN'T BE TRUE.

1209
01:36:00,843 --> 01:36:02,845
BEN? CAROLYN?

1210
01:36:02,845 --> 01:36:05,849
I THINK YOU'D BETTER
COME WITH ME.

1211
01:36:44,387 --> 01:36:46,388
DO THEY KNOW?
UH-UH.

1212
01:36:50,893 --> 01:36:53,896
JACOB, WERE YOU RUNNING
TO SOME--

1213
01:36:53,896 --> 01:36:57,399
NO, I CAME DOWN HERE
TO TELL 'EM THE TRUTH.
EVERYTHING.

1214
01:36:57,399 --> 01:36:59,402
JUST LIKE I TOLD YOU.

1215
01:37:01,403 --> 01:37:03,906
BUT YOU WON'T BELIEVE THIS.

1216
01:37:03,906 --> 01:37:06,408
IT TURNS OUT
THAT IT'S NOT THAT EASY...

1217
01:37:06,408 --> 01:37:08,411
EVEN IF YOU REALLY WANT TO.

1218
01:37:08,411 --> 01:37:11,914
TURNS OUT THAT MY STATEMENT
ISN'T LEGAL UNLESS IT'S
SIGNED BY MY PARENTS.

1219
01:37:14,918 --> 01:37:16,919
DAD?

1220
01:37:18,921 --> 01:37:22,425
YOU WANT THIS NOW.
YOU THINK YOU WANT THIS,
BUT, JAKE,

1221
01:37:22,425 --> 01:37:24,927
YOU'RE STILL UPSET
FROM LAST NIGHT.

1222
01:37:24,927 --> 01:37:28,430
YOU'RE NOT
THINKING CLEARLY.
PLEASE, I AM. I AM.

1223
01:37:28,430 --> 01:37:30,934
I AM THINKING CLEARLY.

1224
01:37:30,934 --> 01:37:34,436
I'LL DO MY BEST TO LEAVE YOU
OUT OF THIS, BUT YOU MIGHT BE
IN SOME TROUBLE TOO.

1225
01:37:34,436 --> 01:37:36,939
AND I'M SORRY.

1226
01:37:36,939 --> 01:37:39,441
IS THAT WHAT YOU--

1227
01:37:39,441 --> 01:37:43,445
OH, GOD, JAKE.
IS THAT WHAT YOU THINK
THIS WAS EVER ABOUT?

1228
01:37:43,445 --> 01:37:45,448
FOR ONE MINUTE?

1229
01:37:47,449 --> 01:37:49,451
I DON'T CARE
WHAT HAPPENS TO ME.

1230
01:37:49,451 --> 01:37:51,954
WHY DO YOU THINK
I'VE BEEN DOING ALL THIS?

1231
01:37:51,954 --> 01:37:55,958
YOU THINK I'M SOME--
SOME KIND OF A SELFISH BULLY?

1232
01:37:55,958 --> 01:37:58,961
I'VE ALWAYS GOT TO HAVE
MY OWN WAY? JAKE.

1233
01:38:00,462 --> 01:38:03,465
NO. DO YOU REMEMBER
WHAT YOU SAID TO ME?

1234
01:38:04,466 --> 01:38:06,969
YOU SAID THE WORST THING
YOU CAN BE CALLED...

1235
01:38:06,969 --> 01:38:10,472
IS SOMEONE WHO DIDN'T
STAND UP FOR HIS FAMILY.

1236
01:38:12,474 --> 01:38:16,479
THIS IS MY WAY.
THIS IS HOW I'VE
GOTTA STAND UP.

1237
01:38:17,980 --> 01:38:20,983
FOR US.
FOR OUR FAMILY.

1238
01:38:26,989 --> 01:38:30,993
THEY'LL PROBABLY TAKE IT
WITH JUST MOM'S SIGNATURE
ON IT.

1239
01:38:31,494 --> 01:38:33,495
BUT I NEED YOU TO DO THIS.

1240
01:38:33,996 --> 01:38:36,498
I NEED YOU
TO DO THIS, PLEASE.

1241
01:38:40,502 --> 01:38:42,504
I NEED THIS FOR ME,
PLEASE.

1242
01:39:04,026 --> 01:39:06,528
I HAD TO BE STRONG.

1243
01:39:08,530 --> 01:39:12,534
I HAD TO ACT CERTAIN
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT YOU
NEEDED FROM ME; ALL OF YOU.

1244
01:39:19,041 --> 01:39:21,043
BUT I CAN'T DO THIS.

1245
01:39:21,043 --> 01:39:23,045
[ Clipboard
Lands On Bench ]

1246
01:39:27,549 --> 01:39:31,553
I CAN NEVER PUT MY HAND
TO ANYTHING THAT WOULD
TAKE YOU AWAY FROM ME.

1247
01:39:32,054 --> 01:39:34,056
I LOVE YOU TOO MUCH, JAKE.

1248
01:39:37,059 --> 01:39:40,062
NOTHING CAN EVER
TAKE ME AWAY FROM YOU.

1249
01:39:44,066 --> 01:39:47,569
OH, SON. MY SON.

1250
01:39:50,072 --> 01:39:52,074
[ Jacob Sobs ]

1251
01:39:55,077 --> 01:39:57,579
I WISH WE COULD GO BACK.

1252
01:39:57,579 --> 01:39:59,581
YEAH.

1253
01:39:59,581 --> 01:40:02,084
I NEVER KNEW
HOW MUCH YOU LOVED ME.

1254
01:40:07,589 --> 01:40:09,091
I NEVER KNEW THAT.

1255
01:40:12,094 --> 01:40:15,097
[ Ben Sobs ]
[ Jacob ]
JUDITH?

1256
01:40:16,598 --> 01:40:18,100
JAKE.

1257
01:40:23,605 --> 01:40:25,607
[ Panos ]
LANGDALE'S A GOOD JUDGE.

1258
01:40:25,607 --> 01:40:28,610
HE'S SMART AND HE'S FAIR,
AND I THINK I MAY HAVE
CONVINCED HIM...

1259
01:40:28,610 --> 01:40:31,113
THAT PRISON TIME
IN THIS CASE WOULD BE
COMPLETELY INAPPROPRIATE.

1260
01:40:31,113 --> 01:40:34,117
I THINK WE GOT
A REAL SHOT.

1261
01:40:34,117 --> 01:40:36,618
BUT YOU SURE DIDN'T
LEAVE ME MUCH TO TRADE WITH.

1262
01:40:37,119 --> 01:40:41,123
I GUESS WE HAVEN'T BEEN
THE MOST HELPFUL CLIENTS
YOU'VE EVER HAD.

1263
01:40:41,123 --> 01:40:43,125
WHY DIDN'T YOU QUIT,
PANOS?

1264
01:40:43,125 --> 01:40:46,128
I TOLD YOU
I'D DEFEND JACOB.

1265
01:40:46,128 --> 01:40:49,132
OR MAYBE I JUST WANTED TO SEE
WHAT YOU TWO WOULD DO NEXT.

1266
01:40:49,132 --> 01:40:51,633
[ Bailiff ]
HEAR YE, HEAR YE.

1267
01:40:51,633 --> 01:40:54,636
THE THIRD DISTRICT COURT
IS NOW IN SESSION.

1268
01:40:54,636 --> 01:40:57,639
THE HONORABLE HENRY LANGDALE
PRESIDING. ALL RISE.

1269
01:40:59,641 --> 01:41:01,643
PLEASE BE SEATED.

1270
01:41:05,147 --> 01:41:07,649
HAVING REVIEWED ALL THE
EVIDENCE AND TESTIMONY...

1271
01:41:08,150 --> 01:41:11,153
IN THE CASE OF THE PEOPLE
VERSUS JACOB RYAN, JUVENILE,

1272
01:41:11,153 --> 01:41:14,656
THIS COURT IS NOW PREPARED
TO RENDER JUDGMENT.

1273
01:41:15,157 --> 01:41:17,659
MARTHA TAVERNER'S DEATH,
IN THE OPINION OF THIS COURT,

1274
01:41:17,659 --> 01:41:21,163
WAS NEITHER PREMEDITATED
NOR DELIBERATELY CAUSED
BY THE DEFENDANT.

1275
01:41:21,163 --> 01:41:24,166
[ Spectators Murmuring ]

1276
01:41:24,166 --> 01:41:28,670
THERE WAS A HEATED ARGUMENT,
A MUTUALLY RECKLESS STRUGGLE,
BUT NO CRIMINAL INTENT.

1277
01:41:28,670 --> 01:41:32,174
[ Murmuring Continues ]

1278
01:41:34,176 --> 01:41:38,680
YOUNG MAN,
I'M ALSO MINDFUL THAT YOU'VE
EXPRESSED DEEP REMORSE;

1279
01:41:38,680 --> 01:41:40,682
THAT YOU'VE MADE A FULL
AND FREE CONFESSION...

1280
01:41:40,682 --> 01:41:45,687
AND DONE SO AT YOUR OWN
INSISTENCE WITHOUT STIPULATING
A PLEA BARGAIN.

1281
01:41:47,189 --> 01:41:51,193
NEVERTHELESS, YOU HAVE
A CLEAR CULPABILITY.

1282
01:41:51,693 --> 01:41:54,696
BY RUNNING AWAY,
BY COVERING UP
YOUR INVOLVEMENT...

1283
01:41:54,696 --> 01:41:56,698
IN THE DEATH
OF MARTHA TAVERNER,

1284
01:41:56,698 --> 01:41:59,701
YOU CAST GRAVE DOUBTS
ON YOUR OWN ACTIONS...

1285
01:42:00,202 --> 01:42:04,206
AND YOU SHORT-CIRCUITED
THE VERY PROTECTIONS
AFFORDED YOU UNDER THE LAW.

1286
01:42:07,209 --> 01:42:09,211
JACOB RYAN, PLEASE RISE.

1287
01:42:14,216 --> 01:42:16,218
- I FIND YOU GUILTY...
- [ Crowd Gasps, Murmurs ]

1288
01:42:16,218 --> 01:42:20,722
OF INVOLUNTARY MANSLAUGHTER
IN THE SECOND DEGREE.

1289
01:42:20,722 --> 01:42:23,725
I SENTENCE YOU TO BE TAKEN
FROM THIS PLACE AND CONFINED...

1290
01:42:24,226 --> 01:42:26,728
AT THE JUVENILE CORRECTION
FACILITY AT FRAMINGHAM...

1291
01:42:26,728 --> 01:42:29,731
FOR A PERIOD
NOT TO EXCEED FIVE YEARS.

1292
01:42:29,731 --> 01:42:33,235
[ Spectators Murmuring ]
[ Gavel Bangs ]

1293
01:42:53,255 --> 01:42:55,757
STILL THINK
IT WAS WORTH IT?

1294
01:43:05,934 --> 01:43:10,939
[ Judith Narrating ]
MY FATHER HAD TO SERVE ALMOST
A YEAR FOR DESTROYING EVIDENCE.

1295
01:43:10,939 --> 01:43:15,444
JACOB WAS RELEASED ON PROBATION
AFTER TWO YEARS.

1296
01:43:15,444 --> 01:43:18,447
HE HAS TO GO TO COUNSELING,
THOUGH.

1297
01:43:20,449 --> 01:43:22,951
SO WE HAVE THEM BACK.

1298
01:43:22,951 --> 01:43:24,953
BUT NONE OF US IS FREE.

1299
01:43:24,953 --> 01:43:27,956
EACH OF US
IS MARKED FOREVER NOW.

1300
01:43:27,956 --> 01:43:30,959
BEFORE... AND AFTER.

1301
01:43:32,461 --> 01:43:34,463
I LOOK AT JACOB NOW...

1302
01:43:34,463 --> 01:43:37,466
AND I THINK ABOUT
HOW DIFFERENT OUR LIVES
MIGHT HAVE BEEN.

1303
01:43:37,466 --> 01:43:41,470
ALL OF US. AND THAT'S
THE SADDEST PART OF ALL.

1304
01:43:41,970 --> 01:43:43,972
[ Jacob ]
HEY, JUDE, LOOK!

1305
01:43:47,476 --> 01:43:49,978
[ Judith ]
BUT LATELY, SOMETIMES,

1306
01:43:49,978 --> 01:43:53,482
I CAN FEEL MYSELF STARTING
TO COME ALIVE AGAIN.

1307
01:43:53,482 --> 01:43:55,484
AND IT'S SCARY, KIND OF.

1308
01:43:55,984 --> 01:43:57,986
I DON'T KNOW
IF THAT'S EVEN ALLOWED.

1309
01:43:59,988 --> 01:44:04,993
MAYBE YOU CAN'T EXPECT
TO KEEP HAPPINESS OUT
OF YOUR LIFE FOREVER,

1310
01:44:04,993 --> 01:44:07,996
ANY MORE THAN TROUBLE.

1311
01:44:07,996 --> 01:44:12,000
YOUR WHOLE LIFE CAN CHANGE
IN A SECOND,

1312
01:44:12,000 --> 01:44:14,503
AND YOU NEVER EVEN KNOW
WHEN IT'S COMING.

